-by-missile-attack%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ET-90M%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20month%2C%20but%20Sergio%20Miller%2C%20an%20independent%20analyst%20formerly%20with%20British%20Army%20intelligence%2C%20estimates%20that%20UVZ%20has%20produced%20perhaps%2040%20T-90Ms%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20Russia's%20'new'%20tanks%20are%20really%20rebuilds%20of%20old%20vehicles%20from%20storage.%20This%20exactly%20mirrors%20the%20situation%20in%20the%20US%2C%20where%20the%20Army's%20new%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.19fortyfive.com%2F2022%2F07%2Fmeet-the-m1a2-sepv3-why-the-abrams-dominates-the-battlefield%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EM1A2%20Abrams%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20in%20fact%20rebuilt%20and%20upgraded%20M1s%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlasobscura.com%2Fplaces%2Fsierra-army-depot%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethousands%20held%20in%20storage%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Sierra%20Army%20Depot%20in%20Doyle%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20vast%20stockpiles%20of%20old%20tanks%2C%20from%20T-90s%20barely%2020%20years%20old%20to%20rusting%20T-62s%20from%20the%201960s.%20These%20offer%20raw%20materials%20for%20refurbishment%20by%20the%20BroneTankovyRemontnyZavod%20(Armored%20Vehicle%20Repair%20Plants)%20or%20BTRZs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20currently%20three%20such%20plants%20for%20tanks%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvk.com%2Fomsktransmash%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOmskTransMash%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Omsk%20Transport%20Machine%20Factory%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvk.com%2F%40585874971-61st-armored-repair-plant%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E61st%20BTRZ%20near%20St%20Petersburg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F103btrz75.ru%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E103rd%20BTRZ%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Siberia.%20Previously%20the%20BTRZs%20were%20mainly%20in%20the%20export%20business%2C%20producing%20tanks%20for%20Venezuela%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20Nicaragua%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Russian%20army.%20Now%20they%20have%20one%20priority%3A%20replacing%20battle%20losses%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ukrinform.ua%2Frubric-ato%2F3565332-minoboroni-rf-planue-stvoriti-se-dva-bronetankovi-zavodi.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwo%20more%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%2071st%20BTRZ%20near%20Rostov%20and%20the%2072nd%20in%20the%20Moscow%20region%20%E2%80%94%20were%20announced%20last%20year%20and%20may%20already%20be%20operational.%20Both%20of%20these%20will%20repair%20damaged%20vehicles%20and%20modernize%20old%20stock.%20There%20are%20also%20at%20least%20ten%20other%20BTRZs%20specializing%20in%20other%20types%20of%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENew%20tanks%20from%20old%20tanks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20T-72%20tank%20in%20Izyum%20Ukraine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6331f61c2675740018b51b40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainians%20load%20a%20Russian%20T-72%20onto%20a%20truck%20outside%20Izyum%20in%20September%202022.%3Cp%3EANATOLII%20STEPANOV%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftopwar.ru%2F18901-103-y-bronetankovyy-remontnyy-zavod.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erefurbishment%20process%20is%20extensive%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Each%20vehicle%20is%20dismantled%20into%20roughly%20a%20thousand%20separate%20parts%20which%20are%20labeled%20to%20indicate%20the%20vehicle%20they%20came%20from%2C%20and%20sent%20to%20specialist%20workshops%20for%20cleaning%20and%20repair%20or%20replacement.%20The%20tank%20body%20is%20scoured%20with%20iron%20shot%20to%20remove%20old%20paint%20and%20rust.%20Engines%20are%20tested%20and%20overhauled%2C%20and%20everything%20else%20is%20tested%20and%20adjusted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERefurbishment%20can%20mean%20more%20than%20just%20getting%20a%20vehicle%20working%20again.%20Turning%20a%20basic%20T-72%20into%20the%20latest%20T-72B3%20involves%20replacing%20the%20original%20engine%20with%20a%20new%20model%20that%20is%2050%25%20more%20powerful%2C%20replacing%20the%20gun%20with%20an%20improved%20version%20capable%20of%20firing%20guided%20missiles%2C%20and%20upgrading%20the%20armor%20with%20a%20layer%20of%20explosive%20reactive%20armor%20blocks.%20New%20sights%2C%20thermal%20imagers%2C%20and%20a%20ballistic%20computer%20and%20digital%20encrypted%20radio%20are%20also%20included.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20process%20turns%20scrapyard%20occupants%20into%20modern%20fighting%20machines%20and%20is%20far%20cheaper%20and%20faster%20than%20building%20new%20vehicles%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20plant%20can%20produce%20roughly%2020%20modernized%20tanks%20per%20month%20under%20ideal%20conditions.%20When%20Defence%20Minister%20Shoigu%20visited%20OmskTransMash%20in%20June%2C%20he%20stated%20they%20he%20was%20instructing%20them%20to%20produce%20153%20T-80%20BVMs%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20or%2025%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20target%20likely%20represents%20the%20upper%20end%20of%20OTM's%20capacity%2C%20which%20they%20are%20unlikely%20to%20reach.%20But%20unlike%20the%20ailing%20UVZ%2C%20OmskTransMash%20does%20appear%20to%20be%20operating%20at%20something%20like%20its%20intended%20level%2C%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fpati_marins64%2Fstatus%2F1688580080581177344%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20video%20apparently%20showing%20railcars%20carrying%20rebuilt%20T-80BVMs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebuilding%20magnifies%20Russia's%20tank%20replacement%20capacity%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelegra.ph%2FNa-skolko-Rossii-hvatit-tankov-i-skolko-mashin-ona-mozhet-proizvodit-i-modernizirovat-ezhegodno-10-24%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%2010%20vehicles%20a%20month%20from%20UVZ%20alone%20to%20more%20like%20120%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20figure%20tallies%20with%20claims%20by%20Putin's%20right-hand%20man%2C%20Dmitry%20Medvedev%2C%20who%20claims%2C%20perhaps%20optimistically%2C%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fclashreport%2Fstatus%2F1638804272442925056%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia%20will%20build%201%2C500%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDigging%20deep%20in%20the%20tank%20mines%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20T-34%20tank%20renovation%20repair%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e3cbb5b698ac0019de917b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221320%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWorkers%20renovate%20and%20repair%20T-34%20tanks%20handed%20over%20by%20Laos%20to%20Russia%20at%20a%20factory%20outside%20St.%20Petersburg%20in%20February%202020.%3Cp%3EOLGA%20MALTSEVA%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EContinuing%20tank%20production%20relies%20entirely%20on%20the%20availability%20of%20raw%20materials.%20The%20inavailability%20of%20imported%20electronics%20has%20hit%20Russia%20hard%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20vehicles%20arriving%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20reportedly%20lack%20thermal%20imagers%20and%20other%20modern%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20not%20have%20much%20significance%2C%20as%20tanks%20are%20used%20more%20as%20mobile%20fire%20support%20and%20as%20artillery%20and%20tank-versus-tank%20encounters%20have%20so%20far%20been%20rare.%20More%20importantly%2C%20Russia's%20supply%20of%20old%20tanks%20for%20rebuilding%20is%20showing%20signs%20of%20running%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20war%2C%20storage%20depots%20around%20Russia%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkyivindependent.com%2Fnational%2Fhow-many-tanks-does-russia-really-have%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehoused%20an%20estimated%2010%2C000%20old%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Of%20these%2C%20a%20small%20proportion%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FChrisO_wiki%2Fstatus%2F1527405190403477517%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperhaps%2010%25%2C%20were%20still%20operable%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20these%20were%20quickly%20put%20into%20service.%20Since%20then%20the%20BTRZs%20have%20been%20busily%20working%20on%20the%20remainder%20and%20either%20turning%20them%20into%20new%20vehicles%20or%20scrapping%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20largest%20single%20armored-vehicle%20storage%20site%20is%20Vagzhanovo%20in%20Buryatia%20close%20to%20the%20border%20with%20Mongolia%2C%20and%20holds%20a%20mixture%20of%20tanks%2C%20personnel%20carriers%2C%20and%20other%20armor.%20Vagzhanovo%20is%20one%20of%20the%20lowest-grade%20mothballing%20facilities.%20The%20highest-rated%20storage%20sites%20are%20climate-controlled%20hangars%2C%20below%20that%20are%20unheated%20hangars%2C%20followed%20by%20storage%20under%20covers%20or%20awnings.%20At%20Vagzhanovo%20the%20vehicles%20are%20stored%20out%20in%20the%20open%2C%20which%20means%20they%20can%20be%20surveyed%20by%20commercial%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moscowtimes.ru%2F2023%2F08%2F07%2Frossiya-vivezla-pochti-polovinu-bronetehniki-s-krupneishei-bazi-hraneniya-a51229%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20report%20in%20the%20Moscow%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war%2C%20the%20Vagzhanovo%20facility%20held%20almost%203%2C840%20vehicles.%20By%20November%202022%2C%20eight%20months%20after%20the%20initial%20invasion%2C%20the%20number%20was%20down%20to%202%2C600%2C%20and%20by%20May%202023%20this%20had%20reduced%20to%202%2C270.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20striking%20that%20a%20large%20number%20of%20vehicles%20were%20withdrawn%20relatively%20rapidly%2C%20presumably%20those%20in%20the%20best%20shape%2C%20which%20could%20most%20easily%20be%20returned%20to%20service.%20The%20rate%20of%20extraction%20has%20dropped%20from%20around%20150%20a%20month%20to%20around%2050%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20should%20be%20more%20BTRZs%20in%20operation.%20One%20theory%20would%20be%20that%20the%20BTRZs%20already%20have%20as%20many%20vehicles%20as%20they%20can%20handle.%20More%20likely%2C%20the%20supply%20of%20suitable%20candidates%20for%20refurbishment%20is%20running%20out%20as%20vehicles%20are%20cannibalized%20to%20get%20a%20few%20of%20them%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRebel44CZ%2Fstatus%2F1688933825248641026%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalyst%20Jakub%20Janovsky%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20open%20source-intelligence%20group%20Oryx%2C%20perhaps%201%2C000%20of%20the%202%2C270%20remaining%20vehicles%20are%20wrecks%20(for%20example%2C%20lacking%20turrets)%2C%20which%20cannot%20be%20repaired%20and%20which%20will%20be%20left%20to%20rust.%20This%20suggests%20that%20Russia%20may%20already%20have%20run%20through%20something%20like%2060%25%20of%20the%20vehicles%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EProduction%20and%20destruction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222984%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dmitry%20Medvedev%20tours%20Russia's%20biggest%20tank%20factory%20in%20the%20Urals%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64555c1502f891001861ab6e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222238%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDmitry%20Medvedev%20tours%20the%20Uralvagonzavod%20tank%20factory%20in%20the%20Urals.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20WWII%2C%20the%20USSR%20managed%20to%20win%20by%20out-producing%20Germany.%20The%20Russians%20took%20massive%20losses%20but%20succeeded%20in%20building%20tanks%20faster%20than%20the%20Nazis%20could%20destroy%20them%20while%20destroying%20more%20enemy%20tanks%20than%20the%20Germans%20could%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20so%20far%20maintained%20a%20significant%20advantage%20in%20tanks%2C%20though%20this%20time%20around%20the%20rate%20of%20production%20lags%20significantly%20behind%20the%20rate%20of%20destruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20meeting%20with%20arms%20suppliers%20in%20March%2C%20Medvedev%20read%20out%20a%20telegram%20originally%20written%20by%20Stalin%20in%201941%20with%20the%20lines%20%26quot%3BI%20ask%20you%20to%20honestly%20and%20on%20time%20fulfill%20orders%20for%20the%20supply%20of%20tank%20hulls%20at%20the%20Chelyabinsk%20Tractor%20Plant.%20Now%20I%20ask%20and%20hope%20that%20you%20will%20fulfill%20your%20duty%20to%20the%20motherland.%20In%20a%20few%20days%2C%20if%20you%20find%20yourself%20violating%20your%20duty%20to%20your%20homeland%2C%20I%20will%20smash%20you%20like%20criminals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20probably%20offers%20an%20idea%20of%20the%20prevailing%20atmosphere%20in%20the%20Kremlin.%20Nobody%20was%20expecting%20this%20to%20turn%20into%20a%20war%20of%20attrition%20in%20which%20the%20number%20of%20old%20T-62s%20Russia%20has%20in%20storage%20would%20be%20a%20factor.%20For%20the%20time%20being%2C%20refurbished%20T-62s%20are%20continuing%20to%20hold%20the%20line%20for%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutin%20must%20be%20sincerely%20hoping%20that%20Western%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20dries%20up%20before%20the%20tank%20boneyards%20give%20up%20the%20last%20of%20their%20usable%20machines%20and%20production%20drops%20down%20to%20effectively%20zero.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EExpert%20biography%20and%20byline%20information%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fdavidhambling%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blan