%20a%20Pell%20Grant%2C%20my%20student%20loans%20would%20be%20forgiven%20up%20to%20%2420%2C000%2C%20if%20I%20paid%20a%20processing%20fee%20of%20%24375.%26quot%3B%20A%20federal%20court%20halted%20the%20operations%20of%20the%20companies%20last%20week%2C%20and%20it%20will%20determine%20whether%20they%20violated%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20could%20not%20immediately%20be%20reached%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%20administration%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-protect-student-loan-borrowers-from-scams-relief-application-2022-10%5C%22%3Epreviously%20warned%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20keep%20an%20eye%20out%20for%20scams%2C%20especially%20with%20confusion%20surrounding%20the%20debt%20relief%20conversation.%20Nearly%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20announced%20up%20to%20%2420%2C000%20in%20debt%20relief%20for%20federal%20borrowers.%20While%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-supreme-court-strikes-down-debt-cancellation-2023-5%5C%22%3Estruck%20down%20the%20plan%20at%20the%20end%20of%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20student-loan%20payments%20are%20still%20resuming%20in%20October%20after%20an%20over%20three-year%20pause%2C%20and%20scammers%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20changing%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20FTC%20accused%20a%20separate%20group%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-scam-getting-debt-relief-ftc-payments-2023-6%5C%22%3Escamming%20borrowers%20out%20of%20%243.3%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20charging%20fees%20for%20debt%20relief%20services%20that%20are%20normally%20free%2C%20and%20it%20send%20payments%20to%2037%2C800%20impacted%20borrowers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-borr