ors-of-the-university-of-missouri-and-capital-region-medical-center-first-amended-petition%23document%2Fp9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esay%20the%20company%20owes%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20%2412%20million%20in%20unpaid%20invoices%20for%20providing%20prisoners%20with%20hospital%20care%2C%20and%20the%20Arizona%20Department%20of%20Corrections%2C%20Rehabilitation%2C%20and%20Reentry%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230322000000000003%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20it's%20spent%20up%20to%20%242%20million%20on%20legal%20costs%20defending%20lawsuits%20the%20department%20claims%20Corizon%20should%20have%20handled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Garcia%20family%20standing%20outside%20between%20two%20hedge%20trees.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64df7499b698ac0019dc33ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221501%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGarcia's%20family%2C%20from%20left%2C%20Daniel%20Jimenez%2C%20his%20son%3B%20Gina%20Macias%2C%20his%20ex-wife%3B%20Belen%20Lowery%2C%20his%20sister%3B%20and%20his%20son%20Hector%20Garcia%2C%20Jr.%20outside%20of%20Jimenez's%20house%20in%20Las%20Cruces.%3Cp%3EAdria%20Malcom%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cast%20of%20characters%20behind%20the%20bankruptcy%20stretches%20from%20Houston%20to%20the%20exurbs%20of%20New%20York's%20Rockland%20County%2C%20sweeping%20up%20a%20hedge%20fund%C2%A0debt%20specialist%20and%20a%20group%20of%20closely%20connected%20Orthodox%20Jewish%20business%20partners%2C%20who%20have%20left%20a%20trail%20of%20lawsuits%20and%20bankruptcies%20in%20their%20wake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tactic%20they%20deployed%20with%20Corizon%20has%20been%20dubbed%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2021-11-04%2Fj-j-takes-second-shot-at-halting-baby-powder-suits-in-bankruptcy%3Fin_source%3Dembedded-checkout-banner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeployed%20the%20novel%20tactic%3C%2Fa%3E%20two%20years%20ago%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20minimize%20a%20wave%20of%20costly%20legal%20claims%20that%20its%20talcum%20powder%20caused%20cancer.%20The%20Two-Step%20involves%20splitting%20a%20company%20into%20parts%20%E2%80%94%20one%20with%20most%20of%20the%20assets%20and%20the%20other%20with%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20liabilities%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20filing%20the%20debt-laden%20company%20into%20bankruptcy.%20J%26amp%3BJ's%20bankruptcy%20was%20shot%20down%20this%20year%20by%20a%20federal%20court.%20For%20now%2C%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20Two-Step%20remains%20an%20open%20question.%20No%20court%20has%20clearly%20established%20its%20legality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Corizon's%20case%2C%20a%20group%20of%20investors%20bought%20out%20the%20company%20in%202021%20and%20within%20months%20created%20a%20new%20company%20called%20YesCare%2C%20home%20to%20most%20of%20Corizon's%20valuable%20assets%20%E2%80%94%20including%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20taxpayer-funded%20contracts%20with%20prisons%20and%20jails.%20The%20liability-laden%20Corizon%20was%20renamed%20Tehum%20and%2C%20in%20February%20of%20this%20year%2C%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-chart%3D%5C%22timeline%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETehum%20has%20transferred%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20entities%20some%20of%20its%20investors%20control%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23921549-attachment-to-the-statement-of-tehums-financial-affairs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company%20filed%20in%20the%20bankruptcy%20case.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20outrageous%20that%20investors'%20profits%20could%20have%20greater%20legal%20protections%20than%20incarcerated%20patients%20and%20their%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20who%20sits%20on%20the%20Senate%20Banking%20Committee%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20fighting%20in%20the%20Senate%20to%20close%20the%20Texas%20Two%20Step%20loophole%20and%20this%20legal%20maneuver%20should%20be%20an%20alarming%20red%20flag.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20of%20Corizon's%20Two-Step%20may%20have%20been%20laid%20bare%20in%20a%20recent%20civil%20complaint.%20It%20describes%20an%20alleged%20meeting%20in%20which%20a%20Tehum%20director%2C%20a%20man%20named%20Isaac%20Lefkowitz%2C%20says%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%20can%20be%20used%20to%20%26quot%3Bforce%20plaintiffs%20into%20accepting%20lower%20settlements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20Corizon%20CEO%2C%20James%20Hyman%2C%20who%20sued%20YesCare%20over%20his%202021%20ouster%20from%20the%20company%2C%20describes%20the%20planned%20Two-Step%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919686-james-hyman-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20his%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20old-fashioned%20bankruptcy%20fraud%20scheme.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYesCare%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.tnmd.93092%2Fgov.uscourts.tnmd.93092.28.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarch%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20denied%20the%20claim%20of%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20taken%20relentless%20questioning%20by%20civil-rights%20attorneys%20representing%20incarcerated%20people%20and%20their%20families%2C%20like%20the%20Garcias%2C%20to%20partially%20uncover%20the%20identities%20of%20Corizon's%20new%20owners.%20And%20their%20identities%20still%20have%20not%20been%20disclosed%20to%20state%20and%20county%20agencies%20that%20have%20signed%20seven-%2C%20eight-%2C%20or%20nine-figure%20contracts%20for%20the%20company's%20healthcare%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20leaked%20documents%2C%20business%20filings%2C%20public-records%20requests%2C%20voluminous%20court%20filings%2C%20and%20interviews%20with%20inside%20sources%2C%20Insider%20has%20been%20able%20to%20identify%20many%20of%20the%20players%20who%20led%20Corizon%20into%20the%20Two-Step.%20Three%20of%20them%20have%20had%20leadership%20roles%20in%20companies%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20Two-Step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20taking%20over%20and%20restructuring%20Corizon%2C%20they%20have%20extended%20that%20strategy%20to%20something%20as%20sensitive%20as%20the%20life%20or%20death%20of%20prisoners%20%E2%80%94%20a%20unique%20set%20of%20patients%20who%20have%20no%20ability%20to%20seek%20second%20opinions%20or%20outside%20care.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20December%2030%2C%202022%2C%20complaint%20filed%20by%20James%20E.%20Hyman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64df8d5fb698ac0019dc5854%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20James%20Hyman%2C%20a%20former%20CEO%20of%20Corizon%2C%20sued%20the%20company%20over%20the%20terms%20of%20his%202021%20ouster%2C%20describing%20Corizon%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20execute%20a%20Texas%20Two-Step%20as%20%E2%80%9Can%20old-fashioned%20bankruptcy%20fraud%20scheme.%E2%80%9D%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20Middle%20District%20of%20Tennessee%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3ETehum's%20representatives%20are%20sitting%20down%20with%20Corizon%20creditors%20today%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20negotiate%20a%20global%20settlement%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20could%20allow%20Corizon's%20buyers%20to%20profit%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20doctors%2C%20universities%2C%20prison%20systems%2C%20and%20the%20hundreds%20of%20inmates%20allegedly%20injured%20or%20killed%20by%20Corizon's%20negligence.%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20several%20creditors%20filed%20a%20motion%20asking%20the%20court%20to%20appoint%20an%20independent%20trustee%2C%20arguing%20that%20Corizon%20and%20Tehum%20had%20engaged%20in%20self-dealing%20tantamount%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bfraudulent%20transfer%26quot%3B%20of%20assets%20outside%20the%20reach%20of%20creditors.%20And%20Insider%20has%20uncovered%20indications%20that%20Lefkowitz%2C%20the%20Tehum%20director%2C%20may%20have%20made%20at%20least%20one%20false%20representation%20under%20oath%20during%20a%20creditor%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20federal%20law%2C%20a%20bankruptcy%20judge%20may%20respond%20to%20evidence%20of%20self-dealing%20or%20perjury%20by%20appointing%20a%20trustee%20to%20take%20control%20of%20the%20bankrupt%20company%2C%20bankruptcy%20experts%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20successful%2C%20Corizon's%20Two-Step%20would%20avoid%20a%20much%20wider%20range%20of%20liabilities%20than%20previous%20companies%20who've%20used%20it%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20injury%20lawsuits%2C%20like%20J%26amp%3BJ%2C%20but%20the%20routine%20debts%20to%20vendors%20that%20companies%20rack%20up%20every%20day.%20If%20the%20company%20succeeds%2C%20it%20provides%20a%20%26quot%3Broadmap%20for%20eliminating%20virtually%20any%20unsecured%20liability%20owed%20by%20any%20corporate%20entity%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20that%20entity%20is%20solvent%2C%26quot%3B%20Ian%20Cross%2C%20a%20Michigan%20civil-rights%20attorney%20who%20represents%20multiple%20prisoners%20who%20have%20sued%20Corizon%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20procedural%20objection%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20wouldn't%20for%20a%20minute%20accept%20it%20if%20they%20understood%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Lynn%20LoPucki%2C%20a%20corporate-law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida%2C%20said%20of%20the%20divisional%20merger%20law%20that%20makes%20the%20Two-Step%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20this%20law%20is%20read%20literally%20and%20people%20take%20advantage%20of%20it%2C%20it%20will%20completely%20change%20the%20American%20economy.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20deadly%20six-day%20sentence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20quality%20of%20Corizon's%20care%20has%20been%20a%20subject%20of%20contention%20for%20many%20years.%20Corizon%20contracts%20were%20canceled%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prisonlegalnews.org%2Fnews%2F2022%2Fmar%2F1%2Fafter-sixth-death-six-years-virginia-jail-cuts-ties-corizon-health%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVirginia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2015%2F06%2F11%2Fnyregion%2Freport-details-failings-of-corizon-rikers-island-health-provider.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20prisoner%20deaths.%20Multiple%20localities%20have%20investigated%20Corizon%2C%20finding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oregonlive.com%2Fcrime%2F2018%2F12%2Frecord-10-million-judgement-awarded-against-corizon-health-in-death-of-washington-county-jail-inmate.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecare%20deficiencies%20in%20Oregon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hiring%20standards%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fstates%2Fnew-york%2Fcity-hall%2Fstory%2F2015%2F06%2Fdoi-report-blasts-corizon-hiring-practices-022905%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20lax%20that%20%26quot%3Bserious%20red%20flags%26quot%3B%20were%20missed.%20And%20thousands%20of%20prisoners%20or%20their%20families%20have%20filed%20lawsuits%20over%20the%20years%20alleging%20that%20medical%20neglect%20by%20Corizon%20harmed%20or%20killed%20them%2C%20some%20resulting%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oregonlive.com%2Fcrime%2F2018%2F12%2Frecord-10-million-judgement-awarded-against-corizon-health-in-death-of-washington-county-jail-inmate.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassive%20judgments%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Victim's%20son%20starring%20out%20a%20window%20with%20a%20strip%20of%20light%20hitting%20his%20face.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dfd68bb698ac0019dcf6fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHector%20Garcia%2C%20Jr.%2C%20wears%20a%20T-shirt%20memorializing%20his%20father.%3Cp%3EAdria%20Malcom%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETracey%20Grissom%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.almd.70032%2Fgov.uscourts.almd.70032.1.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20a%20complaint%20in%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20live%20in%20her%20own%20feces%20for%20four%20months%20after%20Corizon%20contractors%20at%20the%20Alabama%20prison%20where%20she%20was%20held%20failed%20to%20provide%20a%20properly%20fitted%20ostomy%20bag.%20Adree%20Edmo%2C%20a%20transgender%20prisoner%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23909385-adree-edmo-amended-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20a%20claim%20in%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20she%20attempted%20suicide%20after%20Corizon%20providers%20in%20an%20Idaho%20prison%20denied%20her%20gender-affirming%20care.%20William%20Kelly%2C%20one%20of%20Cross'%20clients%2C%20struggles%20with%20constant%20pain%20from%20kidney%20cancer%20that%20progressed%20from%20stage%201%20to%20stage%204%20while%20he%20was%20incarcerated%20in%20Michigan%20prisons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23909384-william-kelly-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%202022%20civil%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Corizon%20failed%20to%20provide%20appropriate%20treatment.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20deteriorating%20fast%20and%20I%20was%20really%20weak.%20I%20knew%20something%20was%20wrong%2C%20was%20extremely%20wrong%20with%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20don't%20give%20you%20any%20kind%20of%20understanding%20of%20what's%20going%20on%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorizon%20disputed%20all%20three%20claims%20in%20court.%20All%20are%20now%20stayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Garcia%2C%2055%2C%20a%20few%20days%20under%20Corizon's%20care%20at%20the%20detention%20facility%20in%20New%20Mexico%20proved%20fatal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarcia%20always%20stood%20out%20in%20his%20family%20as%20a%20kid%2C%20with%20his%20dirty%20blond%20hair%20and%20a%20wide%20smile.%20He%20was%20an%20avid%20basketball%20player%20who%20also%20had%20a%20knack%20for%20the%20arts%2C%20and%20in%20his%20late%20teens%20he%20found%20work%20at%20a%20local%20bakery%2C%20where%20he%20whipped%20up%20fresh%2C%20sugary%20doughnuts%20and%20pastries%20he'd%20bring%20home%20to%20his%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Garcia%20and%20his%20wife%20built%20their%20family%2C%20it%20also%20became%20clear%20that%20he%20was%20struggling%20with%20drug%20addiction%2C%20something%20family%20members%20said%20had%20landed%20him%20in%20jail%20and%20prison%20countless%20times%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Garcia%20saw%20two%20of%20his%20sons%20for%20what%20would%20ultimately%20be%20the%20last%20time%20in%20August%20of%202019%2C%20he%20had%20just%20been%20released%20from%20jail.%20He%20walked%20a%20mile%20to%20the%20home%20of%20his%20son%20Hector%20Garcia%20Jr.%20to%20say%20how%20sorry%20he%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20two%20hours%20that%20day%2C%20Garcia%20sat%20down%20over%20pizza%20with%20Hector%20Jr.%20and%20his%20younger%20brother%20Ricky%20as%20he%20apologized%20for%20his%20years%20of%20addiction%20and%20the%20ways%20it%20had%20disrupted%20their%20lives.%20When%20Hector%20Jr.%20dropped%20his%20dad%20at%20his%20grandma's%20house%20that%20evening%2C%20Garcia%20said%20that%20he%20loved%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FVpUckEZ7-sVNJtny9.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Hector%20Garcia's%20final%20days%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Garcia's%20family%20heard%20that%20he%20was%20back%2C%20three%20weeks%20later%2C%20at%20the%20Do%C3%B1a%20Ana%20County%20Detention%20Center%2C%20they%20didn't%20think%20much%20of%20it.%20One%20of%20his%20friends%20was%20pulled%20over%20while%20driving%20and%2C%20during%20the%20stop%2C%20law-enforcement%20officers%20discovered%20that%20Garcia%2C%20in%20the%20passenger's%20seat%2C%20had%20an%20outstanding%20warrant%20stemming%20from%20a%20shoplifting%20charge.%20Unable%20to%20afford%20the%20%24242%20fine%2C%20he%20was%20booked%20for%20a%20six-day%20sentence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20figured%20he's%20going%20to%20stay%20there%20for%20a%20few%20days%20and%20pay%20his%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20his%20sister%2C%20Belen%20Lowery%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20he%20wasn't%20going%20to%20ask%20us%20for%20money.%26quot%3B%20That%20weekend%20she%20bought%20a%20futon%20for%20her%20brother%20so%20he'd%20have%20a%20place%20to%20sleep%20in%20their%20mother's%20new%20house%20following%20his%20release.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20never%20got%20to%20sleep%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221580%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20August%204%2C%202019%20incident%20report%20from%20the%20Do%C3%B1a%20Ana%20Detention%20Center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64df8bcfb698ac0019dc562c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22688%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20August%202019%20incident%20report%20from%20the%20Do%C3%B1a%20Ana%20County%20Detention%20Center%20documents%20Hector%20Garcia's%20collapse.%3Cp%3EDo%C3%B1a%20Ana%20County%2C%20New%20Mexico%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHector%20Jr.%20will%20never%20forget%20finding%20his%20spirited%20father%20unconscious%20in%20a%20hospital%20bed%2C%20hooked%20up%20to%20multiple%20tubes.%20He%20died%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Hector%20Jr.%20was%20absorbing%20the%20news%2C%20he%20said%2C%20a%20hospital%20nurse%20approached%20him%20to%20say%20she%20found%20the%20detention%20center's%20treatment%20of%20his%20father%20suspicious%20and%20suggested%20that%20the%20family%20hire%20a%20lawyer.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.nmd.461245%2Fgov.uscourts.nmd.461245.1.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20a%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20family%20against%20Corizon%2C%20the%20warden%2C%20and%20other%20defendants%20claiming%20that%20medical%20workers%20employed%20by%20Corizon%20had%20violated%20Garcia's%20Eighth%20Amendment%20rights%20by%20denying%20him%20adequate%20medical%20care.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawsuits%20against%20prisons%20and%20jails%20are%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20win%2C%20but%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20the%20family's%20attorney%2C%20Matt%20Coyte%2C%20thought%20he%20had%20an%20ironclad%20case.%20Medical%20personnel%20had%20admitted%20in%20depositions%20that%20they%20violated%20standard%20of%20care%20when%20treating%20Garcia%2C%20and%20Coyte%20had%20obtained%20surveillance%20video%20that%20he%20said%20documented%20extreme%20forms%20of%20medical%20negligence.%20Corizon%20has%20denied%20the%20Garcias'%20allegations.%20But%20Coyte%20told%20Insider%20he%20expected%20to%20win%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20damages%20at%20an%20August%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20six%20months%20before%20the%20Garcia%20family%20was%20scheduled%20to%20have%20their%20day%20in%20court%2C%20Corizon%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy.%20Their%20lawsuit%2C%20along%20with%20hundreds%20of%20others%2C%20was%20indefinitely%20stayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20debt%20specialist%20is%20put%20in%20charge%20of%20prisoner%20care%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHealthcare%20in%20correctional%20institutions%20began%20to%20be%20widely%20outsourced%20and%20privatized%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigates%2Fspecial-report%2Fusa-jails-privatization%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1980s%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20recent%20years%20the%20field%20has%20been%20dominated%20by%20a%20few%20major%20firms%2C%20Corizon%20among%20them.%20Founded%20in%201978%20as%20Prison%20Health%20Services%2C%20Inc.%2C%20the%20company%20changed%20its%20name%20to%20Corizon%20in%202011%20after%20merging%20with%20a%20competitor%2C%20making%20it%20the%20country's%20largest%20private%20prison%20healthcare%20provider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20Corizon%20told%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.floridabulldog.org%2F2013%2F10%2Fflorida-prison-officials-didnt-ask-companies-didnt-tell-about-hundreds-of-malpractice-cases%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlorida%20news%20outlet%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company%20had%20been%20a%20defendant%20in%20660%20malpractice%20lawsuits%20over%20the%20previous%20five%20years.%20In%202015%2C%20Corizon%20lost%20a%20%24154%20million%20contract%20with%20New%20York%20City%3B%20four%20years%20later%20it%20lost%20a%20%24200%20million%20contract%20with%20Arizona.%20A%20New%20York%20state%20panel%20found%20Corizon's%20treatment%20%26quot%3Bso%20incompetent%20and%20inadequate%20as%20to%20shock%20the%20conscience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20revenue%20instability%20resulted%20in%20a%20series%20of%20ownership%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%202014%2C%20Corizon%20had%2014%2C000%20employees%2C%20and%20the%20company%20brought%20in%20%241.5%20billion%20the%20following%20year.%20But%20by%20June%202020%2C%20payroll%20had%20dropped%20to%205%2C000%20employees%20responsible%20for%20annual%20revenue%20of%20about%20%24800%20million%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.ph%2FbiNtM%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Nashville%20business%20journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20when%20investment%20firm%20BlueMountain%20Capital%20Management%20sold%20Corizon%20for%20an%20undisclosed%20sum%20to%20a%20small%20Florida%20investor%20called%20Flacks%20Group.%20In%20late%202021%20the%20company%20lost%20its%20two%20largest%20remaining%20contracts%2C%20with%20corrections%20departments%20in%20Michigan%20and%20Missouri%2C%20worth%20more%20than%20%24400%20million%20in%20annual%20revenue.%20Revenue%20would%20shrink%20to%20roughly%20%24600%20million%20that%20year%2C%20and%20keep%20falling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202021%2C%20Flacks%20Group%20offloaded%20Corizon%20to%20the%20unidentified%20buyers%20who%20would%20execute%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step.%20Even%20Hyman%2C%20then%20Corizon's%20CEO%2C%20didn't%20know%20who%20the%20buyers%20were%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919686-james-hyman-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20lawsuit%20he%20filed%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20YesCare%20and%20other%20parties%20over%20his%20severance%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20was%20dismissed%20in%20July.%20He%20refers%20to%20them%20in%20the%20suit%20as%20%26quot%3Bone%20or%20more%20persons%20or%20entities%20whose%20identities%20are%20unknown%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bunknown%20buyer.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20sale%20could%20have%20been%20a%20chance%20to%20turn%20the%20beleaguered%20correctional%20healthcare%20company%20around%20and%20provide%20quality%20care%20to%20its%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20incarcerated%20patients.%20(As%20of%20January%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noo