he%20other%2C%20called%20CHS%20TX%2C%20Inc.%2C%20got%20the%20old%20Corizon's%20C-suite%20and%20more%20than%20%24300%20million%20in%20public%20contracts.%20It%20would%20conduct%20business%20under%20the%20name%20YesCare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETirschwell%20was%20named%20CEO%20of%20YesCare%2C%20where%20she%20quickly%20got%20to%20work%20reaching%20out%20to%20the%20state%20and%20county%20agencies%20whose%20contracts%20with%20Corizon%20had%20suddenly%20moved%20to%20the%20new%20company.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYesCare%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20detailed%20queries.%20Jason%20S.%20Brookner%2C%20an%20attorney%20for%20Tehum%2C%20provided%20a%20brief%20statement.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20proceeding%20with%20court-ordered%20mediation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20substantially%20all%20of%20these%20issues%20will%20be%20addressed.%20We%20have%20no%20further%20comment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20mysterious%20'healthcare%20conglomerate'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOkaloosa%20County%2C%20a%20midsize%20county%20in%20Florida's%20panhandle%2C%20has%20been%20working%20with%20Corizon%20for%20decades.%20In%20May%202022%2C%20the%20director%20of%20corrections%20there%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23917102-okaloosa-yescare-announcement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceived%20an%20email%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20Corizon%20staffer%20sharing%20an%20announcement%20from%20Tirschwell%20that%20described%20YesCare%20as%20a%20new%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMonday%20morning%2C%20we%20will%20be%20announcing%20that%20the%20dedicated%20employees%20of%20Corizon%20Health%20have%20teamed%20up%20with%20a%20healthcare%20conglomerate%20to%20create%20YesCare%2C%20launching%20our%20new%20vision%20for%20correctional%20healthcare%20nationwide%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20left%20the%20agencies%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20who%2C%20exactly%2C%20they%20were%20now%20doing%20business%20with.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYesCare%20Holdings%20LLC%20%E2%80%94%20the%20majority%20owner%20of%20YesCare's%20parent%20company%20%E2%80%94%20had%20been%20set%20up%20only%20two%20days%20before%20the%20email%20was%20sent.%20The%20message%20didn't%20name%20the%20%26quot%3Bhealthcare%20conglomerate%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20two%20contracting%20agencies%2C%20including%20Do%C3%B1a%20Ana%20County%2C%20told%20Insider%20they%20were%20not%20made%20aware%20of%20the%20conglomerate's%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubsequent%20emails%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23917103-okaloosa-county-emails%23document%2Fp4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emention%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20new%20ownership.%20But%20in%20referencing%20a%20%26quot%3BCorizon%20rebranding%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bour%20announcement%20on%20our%20name%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20YesCare%20employees%20led%20Okaloosa%20officials%20to%20believe%20the%20change%20was%20a%20rebrand%2C%20not%20a%20change%20in%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221096%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22June%202%2C%202022%20email%20from%20Karen%20Davies%20of%20YesCare%20to%20Eric%20Esmond%2C%20an%20Okaloosa%20County%20corrections%20official%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e0ff9dbd98a600197a23fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22685%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20June%202022%20email%20from%20YesCare%20to%20an%20Okaloosa%20County%20corrections%20official%20mentions%20Corizon's%20new%20ownership%20but%20refers%20to%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bname%20change%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20rebrand.%3Cp%3EOkaloosa%20County%2C%20Florida%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20Okaloosa%20officials%20expressed%20confusion.%20The%20name%20%26quot%3BYesCare%26quot%3B%20didn't%20show%20up%20in%20the%20state's%20online%20business%20portal%20%E2%80%94%20an%20indication%20that%20it%20wasn't%20registered%20to%20do%20business%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCan%20you%20please%20take%20care%20of%20that%20and%20provide%20me%20an%20email%20confirmation%20when%20complete%3F%26quot%3B%20a%20senior%20contracts%20and%20lease%20coordinator%20for%20the%20county%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23917269-okaloosa-county-emails%23document%2Fp1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemailed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20YesCare%20staffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20address%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20YesCare%20staffer%20replied.%20%26quot%3BMany%20thanks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENick%20Tomecek%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Okaloosa%20County%2C%20told%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20despite%20any%20organization%20changes%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20the%20same%20staff%20and%20providers%20that%20we%20have%20worked%20with%20for%20years%26quot%3B%20and%20their%20contract%20was%20subject%20to%20%26quot%3Bmeticulous%20scrutiny%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bprotects%20the%20County's%20interests.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20communications%20mentioning%20a%20name%20change%20went%20out%20to%20other%20public%20agencies%20that%20were%20doing%20business%20with%20Corizon%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Wyoming%20Department%20of%20Corrections%20and%20counties%20in%20Florida%20and%20New%20Mexico.%20But%20experts%20said%20the%20divisional%20merger%20signaled%20a%20change%20in%20control%20that%20should%20have%20triggered%20more%20robust%20disclosure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you've%20made%20differences%20in%20arrangements%20that%20go%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20'Who%20am%20I%20working%20with%20on%20this%20contract%3F'%20then%20that's%20not%20a%20name%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Christopher%20Atkinson%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20in%20the%20public-administration%20program%20at%20the%20University%20of%20West%20Florida%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20obtained%20contracts%20or%20correspondence%20from%2019%20county%2