%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPerigrove%20shares%20the%20Suffern%20address%20with%20numerous%20other%20companies.%20Incorporation%20records%20list%20Gefner%20as%20the%20organizer%20for%20dozens%20of%20Perigrove-related%20entities%2C%20with%20names%20like%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919683-perigrove-1021a-llc-articles-of-organization%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPerigrove%201021A%20LLC%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919684-perigrove-1028-llc-articles-of-organization%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPerigrove%201028%20LLC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20all%20registered%20at%20the%20office%20above%20the%20auto-parts%20store.%20The%20unassuming%20office%20space%20near%20a%20Kosher%20grocery%20store%20and%20an%20Orthodox%20synagogue%20is%20also%20the%20home%20of%20Perigrove%201018%20LLC%2C%20the%20ultimate%20parent%20company%20of%20Tehum.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGefner%20is%20listed%20as%20the%20company's%20organizer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPotential%20signs%20of%20perjury%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Corrections%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23911031-yescares-alabama-department-of-corrections-program-proposal%23document%2Fp17%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposal%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20YesCare%20submitted%20last%20year%20contained%20another%20pivotal%20detail%20about%20the%20company's%20backing%2C%20one%20Lefkowitz%20avoided%20revealing%20under%20intense%20questioning%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYesCare%20says%20it%20is%20managed%20and%20financially%20supported%20by%20a%20company%20called%20Geneva%20Consulting%20LLC%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20wholly-owned%20subsidiary%20of%20the%20Genesis%20Healthcare%20group%20of%20companies.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeneva%20Consulting%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919685-geneva-consulting-llc-certificate-of-registration%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincorporated%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20with%20Gefner%20as%20general%20partner%20and%20registered%20to%20the%20same%207%20World%20Trade%20Center%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20month%20after%20Geneva%20was%20formed%2C%20Hyman%20discovered%20something%20that%20alarmed%20him%3A%20Lefkowitz%2C%20as%20a%20representative%20of%20Corizon's%20new%20owners%2C%20had%20signed%20off%20on%20a%20%243%20million%20payment%20to%20Geneva%20for%20future%20services%20described%20only%20as%20%26quot%3Bcorporate%20restructuring.%26quot%3B%20Hyman%20asked%20Lefkowitz%20about%20the%20transaction%2C%20he%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919686-james-hyman-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20was%20immediately%20terminated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELefkowitz%20later%20explained%2C%20on%20a%20creditors%20call%20in%20June%2C%20that%20Geneva%20served%20as%20an%20intermediary%20between%20M2%20LoanCo%2C%20the%20lender%2C%20and%20Tehum%2C%20the%20company%20Corizon%20saddled%20with%20its%20debts%2C%20making%20payments%20on%20behalf%20of%20Tehum%20to%20various%20vendors.%20He%20said%20it%20was%20his%20job%20to%20review%20invoices%20before%20Geneva%20sent%20payments%20from%20its%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20said%20he%20held%20no%20official%20title%20with%20Geneva%20nor%20received%20any%20compensation.%20And%20Lefkowitz%20said%20under%20oath%20on%20the%20June%20creditor's%20call%20that%20he%20didn't%20know%20the%20identity%20of%20Geneva's%20principals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20sworn%20testimony%20may%20be%20false.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20motion%20in%20the%20%2412%20million%20lawsuit%20filed%20against%20Tehum%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Missouri%20Health%20Care%20system%20and%20the%20local%20hospital%20over%20nonpayment%2C%20Lefkowitz%20had%20a%20controlling%20interest%20in%20Geneva.%20In%20a%20motion%20filed%20in%20June%20to%20force%20compliance%20with%20a%20subpoena%2C%20lawyers%20for%20the%20unsecured%20creditors%20committee%20cite%20Geneva's%20attorney%20saying%20his%20%26quot%3Bclient%20contact%26quot%3B%20there%20was%20Lefkowitz.%20According%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230623000000000005%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattachment%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Geneva's%20exhibit%20list%2C%20Lefkowitz%20has%C2%A0one%20of%20just%2011%20email%20addresses%20at%20Geneva.%20He%20is%20listed%20on%20a%20company%20website%20as%20a%20director%20of%20Genesis%20Healthcare%2C%20Geneva's%20owner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20Genesis%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919674-continued-section-341-meeting-of-creditors%23document%2Fp83%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMay%20creditors%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lefkowitz%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20possible%2C%20I'm%20not%20100%20percent%20certain%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20company%20has%20an%20investment%20in%20Perigrove%201018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenesis%20Healthcare%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20nursing-home%20systems%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20with%20more%20than%20200%20facilities%20in%2021%20states.%20It's%20also%20another%20deeply%20troubled%20company%3A%20In%202021%2C%20after%20several%20years%20of%20poor%20financial%20performance%2C%20Genesis%20was%20taken%20over%20and%20delisted%20from%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20230707144840%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.genesishcc.com%2Fabout-us%2Fpress%2Fpress-releases%2Fgenesis-healthcare-announces-strategic-restructuring-steps-strengthen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGenesis%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20money%20for%20the%20purchase%20came%20from%20an%20affiliate%20of%20a%20private-equity%20firm%20called%20Pinta%20Capital%20Partners%20that%20was%20founded%20in%202012%20by%20David%20Harrington%20and%20Landau%20%E2%80%94%20the%20investor%20who%20Flacks%20said%20was%20part%20of%20the%20group%20who%20purchased%20Corizon.%20Landau%20was%20later%20described%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprospect.org%2Fhealth%2Fdespite-pandemic-carnage-predatory-nursing-home-financiers-thriving%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20American%20Prospect%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20a%20%26quot%3Bserial%20liar%20with%20a%20history%20of%20conning%20his%20way%20into%20nursing%20home%20takeovers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELandau%20gained%20notoriety%20several%20years%20ago%20for%20his%20role%20in%20a%20scandal%20during%20the%20Bill%20de%20Blasio%20administration.%20That's%20when%20another%20Landau%20company%20purchased%20a%20former%20219-bed%20Lower%20East%20Side%20nursing%20home%20called%20Rivington%20House.%20City%20officials%20lifted%20deed%20restrictions%20on%20the%20property%20after%20Landau%20made%20a%20commitment%20to%20local%20officials%20that%20there'd%20be%20no%20changes%20for%20residents.%20But%20he%20quickly%20reneged%20and%20sold%20the%20property%20to%20developers%2C%20netting%20%2472%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELandau%20has%20ties%20with%20both%20Lefkowitz%20and%20Gefner.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhindenburgresearch.com%2Fwelltower%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHindenburg%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Gefner%20once%20worked%20for%20Pinta%20Capital.%20An%20archived%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20160115020940%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fjacklefkowitz.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2009%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20Lefkowitz%20and%20Landau%20shaking%20hands%20and%20smiling%20with%20then%20New%20York%20Gov.%20David%20Paterson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20strategy%20'to%20benefit%20insider%20individuals'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complex%20web%20of%20business%20relationships%20appears%20to%20have%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230630000000000003%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eself-dealing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20were%20Corizon%20and%20YesCare's%20contracts%20with%20the%20Goldberger-controlled%20United%20Staffing%20Solutions.%20There%20was%20the%20%243%20million%20consultancy%20between%20Corizon%20and%20Geneva%20whose%20discovery%20may%20have%20gotten%20Hyman%20fired.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Alabama%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23911031-yescares-alabama-department-of-corrections-program-proposal%23document%2Fp59%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposal%20document%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20YesCare%20also%20entered%20into%20an%20agreement%20with%20Geneva%2C%20paying%20Geneva%20to%20provide%20administrative%20support%20services%2C%20capital%20financing%2C%20and%20bonding%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider's%20analysis%20of%20financial%20records%20filed%20by%20Tehum%20in%20bankruptcy%20court%20shows%20that%20since%20the%20new%20buyers%20purchased%20Corizon%2C%20the%20company%20has%20transferred%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230804000000000023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2448%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20entities%20controlled%20by%20Lefkowitz%20and%20Gefner%2C%20potentially%20limiting%20the%20pool%20of%20funds%20available%20for%20settling%20claims%20with%20creditors%20like%20the%20Garcias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Corizon%20gave%20Perigrove%20%246%20million%20from%20April%20to%20June%202022%2C%20the%20period%20in%20which%20the%20company%20became%20Tehum.%20And%20Corizon%20sent%20%247.5%20million%20to%20another%20Gefner%20company%2C%20DG%20Realty%2C%20in%20December%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(A%20footnote%20indicates%20Tehum%20has%20also%20received%20%2424%20million%20from%20five%20parties%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20break%20down%20the%20payments.)%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20egregious%20form%20of%20the%20Two-Step%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20thing%20that%20bankruptcy%20is%20designed%20to%20prevent%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Roe%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Law%20School%20who%20teaches%20bankruptcy%20and%20corporate%20law%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BA%20transfer%20of%20assets%20to%20our%20friends%20or%20ourselves%2C%20and%20to%20avoid%20paying%20liabilities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOved%2C%20Gefner's%20attorney%2C%20said%20in%20the%20statement%2C%20%26quot%3BCorizon%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20filing%20bankruptcy%20when%20it%20was%20acquired%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3BCorizon%20has%20done%20nothing%20wrong%20by%20availing%20itself%20of%20the%20same%20laws%20and%20protections%20afforded%20every%20other%20company%20in%20this%20country%20and%20any%20implication%20to%20the%20contrary%20is%20false.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ACLU%2C%20Public%20Justice%2C%20and%20other%20civil-rights%20organizations%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230517000000000004%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20an%20amicus%20brief%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20May%20on%20behalf%20of%20pro%20se%20incarcerated%20plaintiffs.%20In%20it%2C%20they%20argue%20that%20the%20level%20of%20self-dealing%20among%20the%20principals%20has%20weakened%20the%20ability%20of%20creditors%20to%20repossess%20assets%20that%20may%20have%20been%20wrongly%20moved%20out%20of%20their%20reach.%20Lawyers%20for%20the%20unsecured%20creditors%20also%20argued%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230629000000000005%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJune%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%20opposing%20Tehum's%20attempts%20to%20draw%20out%20the%20timeline%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bthis%20bankruptcy%20process%20is%20serving%20to%20benefit%20insider%20individuals%20and%20affiliated%20entities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoPucki%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Florida%20scholar%2C%20said%20that%20the%20case%2C%20if%20it's%20resolved%20in%20favor%20of%20Tehum's%20owners%2C%20could%20signal%20%26quot%3Ba%20fundamental%20change%20in%20the%20law%20governing%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20effectively%20rewriting%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20bankruptcy%20code%20laid%20down%20by%20Congress%20over%20a%20century%20ago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20this%20case%20shows%2C%20corporations%20will%20keep%20trying%20to%20manipulate%20bankruptcy%20to%20game%20the%20justice%20system%20unless%20Congress%20puts%20a%20stop%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Dick%20Durbin%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202022%2C%20just%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20divisional%20merger%20that%20created%20YesCare%2C%20Lefkowitz%20was%20trying%20another%20maneuver%20to%20siphon%20money%20out%20of%20the%20cash-strapped%20Corizon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20allegations%20in%20a%202022%20lawsuit%2C%20he%20and%20two%20business%20partners%2C%20including%20someone%20identified%20on%20a%20wire%20transfer%20as%20%26quot%3BDAVID%2C%26quot%3B%20planned%20to%20purchase%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20COVID%20test%20kits%20from%20a%20company%20called%20Seven%20Trade%2C%20registered%20to%20the%20same%20World%20Trade%20Center%20address%20and%20organized%20by%20Gefner.%20Lefkowitz%20and%20Gefner%20describe%20themselves%20in%20legal%20documents%20as%20its%20director%20and%20sole%20member%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%2C%20filed%20by%20Seven%20Trade%20against%20the%20test-kit%20supplier%2C%20says%20they%20planned%20to%20resell%20the%20tests%20to%20Corizon%20at%20a%2057%25%20markup.%20If%20the%20deal%20hadn't%20fallen%20through%2C%20it%20would%20have%20netted%20them%20almost%20%241.2%20million%3B%20Seven%20Trade%20won%20a%20%242.9%20million%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20Cross%2C%20the%20civil-rights%20attorney%2C%20joined%20other%20creditors%20in%20filing%20a%20motion%20for%20the%20court%20to%20appoint%20an%20independent%20trustee%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20Seven%20Trade%20episode%20%26quot%3Bis%20perhaps%20the%20clearest%20available%20evidence%20that%20Mr.%20Lefkowitz%20is%20unlikely%20to%20act%20as%20a%20responsible%20fiduciary.%26quot%3B%20(In%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230728000000000007%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobjection%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20attorneys%20for%20Tehum%20said%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bdisputes%20the%20implications%20or%20the%20specific%20allegations.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Debtor's%20directors%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20motion%20said%20of%20Tehum%2C%20%26quot%3Bengaged%20and%20attempted%20to%20engage%20in%20various%20self-dealing%20transactions%20while%20the%20Debtor%20was%20insolvent%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20the%20Seven%20Trade%20deal%20and%20Tehum's%20%26quot%3Bpayment%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20Geneva%20Consulting%20LLC%2C%20a%20newly-formed%20entity%20controlled%20by%20insiders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221812%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20excerpt%20from%20a%20June%2030%2C%202023%2C%20motion%20to%20appoint%20a%20Chapter%2011%20trustee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dfa130bd98a60019794cbb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22764%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20June%20of%20this%20year%2C%20Corizon%20creditors%20filed%20a%20motion%20asking%20the%20court%20to%20appoint%20an%20independent%20trustee%2C%20arguing%20that%20Tehum%E2%80%99s%20directors%20engaged%20in%20%E2%80%9Cself-dealing.%E2%80%9D%3Cp%3EUS%20Bankruptcy%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202022%2C%20just%20three%20months%20after%20Seven%20Trade%20filed%20suit%20and%20right%20around%20the%20time%20of%20the%20divisional%20merger%2C%20Tirschwell%2C%20YesCare's%20founding%20CEO%2C%20was%20looking%20to%20sign%20up%20new%20business.%20YesCare%20had%20its%20eyes%20on%20one%20particularly%20lucrative%20call%20for%20bids%3A%20the%20one%20from%20the%20state%20of%20Alabama.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Corrections%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20notorious%20prison%20systems%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20department%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wbrc.com%2F2019%2F01%2F11%2Finside-federal-investigation-alabama-prisons%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20federal%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202016%20over%20horrific%20conditions%20and%20pervasive%20violence%2C%20and%20it's%20still%20fighting%20a%20class-action%20lawsuit%20filed%20in%202014%20by%20the%20Southern%20Poverty%20Law%20Center%20over%20claims%20of%20inadequate%20healthcare.%20The%20stakes%20were%20high%20for%20whoever%20would%20come%20in%20to%20handle%20medical%20care%20for%20the%20system's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoc.alabama.gov%2Fdocs%2FAnnualRpts%2F2021%2520Annual%2520Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2018%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20reviewing%20five%20bids%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.al.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F07%2Falabama-department-of-corrections-picks-new-medical-mental-health-care-provider.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20state%20awarded%20a%20billion-dollar%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20YesCare%2C%20a%20company%20that%20had%20been%20established%20only%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20earlier.%20The%20decision%20was%20shrouded%20in%20controversy.%20A%20corrections%20department%20attorney%20acknowledged%20a%20potential%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.alreporter.com%2F2023%2F02%2F07%2Fbillion-dollar-prison-healthcare-contract-halted-after-claims-of-undue-influence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econflict%20of%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20Wexford%2C%20a%20competitor%20for%20the%20massive%20bid%2C%20alleged%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20governor%20obtained%20by%20Insider%20that%20YesCare's%20CEO%20%E2%80%94%20then%20Tirschwell%20%E2%80%94%20violated%20a%20%26quot%3Bcone%20of%20silence%26quot%3B%20period%20by%20having%20dinner%20with%20the%20department's%20top%20corrections%20official%20during%20the%20bidding%20process.%20Alabama%20rebid%20the%20contract%2C%20but%20YesCare%20prevailed%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20another%20striking%20revelation%20in%20YesCare's%20proposal%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20hints%20at%20why%20the%20group%20of%20investors%20wanted%20to%20take%20over%20Corizon%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYesCare%20and%20Geneva%20Consulting%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23911031-yescares-alabama-department-of-corrections-program-proposal%23document%2Fp40%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20proposal%20explains%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20intend%20to%20create%20a%20prison-to-nursing-home%20pipeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20say%20YesCare%20plans%20to%20develop%20and%20manage%20skilled%20nursing%20facilities%20to%20house%20medically%20fragile%20older%20people%20on%20medical%20furlough%20from%20prison%2C%20on%20parole%2C%20or%20who%20recently%20finished%20their%20sentence%2C%20creating%20a%20direct%20path%20from%20the%20prisons%20to%20their%20centers.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23911031-yescares-alabama-department-of-corrections-program-proposal%23document%2Fp141%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposal%20lists%3C%2Fa%3E%2011%20facilities%20across%20Alabama%2C%20nine%20of%20them%20run%20by%20Genesis%2C%20that%20collectively%20can%20house%20more%20than%20700%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20more%20cases%20than%20not%2C%20releasing%20patients%20are%20denied%20access%20to%20nursing%20homes%20due%20to%20their%20history%20of%20violence%20or%20their%20infectious%20disease%20status%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20proposal%20says%2C%20referencing%20a%20chart%20of%20the%20Genesis%20facilities.%20%26quot%3BYesCare%20has%20access%20to%20the%20facilities%20below%20to%20assist%20the%20ADOC%20with%20nursing%20home%20placements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20describes%20the%20arrangement%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20innovative%20means%20to%20transfer%20significant%20healthcare%20costs%20away%20from%20State%20budgets.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeven%20of%20the%20nine%20Genesis%20facilities%20listed%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.propublica.org%2Fnursing-homes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20ProPublica's%3C%2Fa%3E%20nursing-home%20database%2C%20received%20%26quot%3BD%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BE%26quot%3B%20%2C%20%26quot%3BF%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3BJ%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BK%26quot%3B%20ratings%20from%20the%20federal%20Centers%20for%20Medicare%20and%20Medicaid%20Services%2C%20on%20a%20scale%20of%20A%20to%20L.%20Insider%20found%20at%20least%2080%20documented%20deficiencies%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years%20in%20which%20these%20facilities%20failed%20to%20meet%20care%20requirements%2C%20resulting%20in%20over%20%2444%2C000%20in%20fines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBankruptcy%20was%20in%20her%20playbook%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20new%20owners%20quietly%20took%20over%20Corizon%2C%20they%20appointed%20someone%20as%20CEO%20with%20no%20prior%20experience%20in%20corrections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESara%20Tirschwell%2C%20a%20Texas%20native%20with%20piercing%20hazel%20eyes%2C%20spent%20much%20of%20her%20career%20at%20Davidson%20Kempner%2C%20the%20distressed-debt%20pioneer.%20There%2C%20she%20served%20as%20interim%20CFO%20for%20an%20addiction-treatment%20center%20in%20Maine%2C%20sat%20on%20the%20board%20of%20a%20cannabis%20transport%20company%2C%20and%20helped%20to%20restructure%20an%20Israeli%20automotive%20supplier.%20She%20went%20on%20to%20become%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20Quest%20Turnaround%20Advisors%2C%20a%20firm%20specializing%20in%20managing%20flailing%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20before%20joining%20Corizon%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20run%20for%20New%20York%20City%20mayor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20all%20accounts%2C%20it%20was%20a%20spectacular%20debacle.%20She%20failed%20even%20to%20collect%20enough%20signatures%20to%20get%20onto%20the%20Republican%20primary%20ballot.%20And%20yet%20she%20may%20have%20violated%20campaign-finance%20laws%2C%20according%20to%20a%20July%202022%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919668-new-york-city-campaign-finance-board-notification-letter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20submitted%20to%20the%20city's%20Campaign%20Finance%20Board%2C%20by%20failing%20to%20properly%20report%20expenditures%20and%20in-kind%20contributions.%20When%20a%20board%20employee%20had%20contacted%20her%20some%20months%20earlier%20with%20questions%20about%20outstanding%20liabilities%20owed%20by%20her%20campaign%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23917291-new-york-city-campaign-finance-board-contact-record%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20notes%20of%20the%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Tirschwell%20responded%20that%20she%20%26quot%3Bwould%20simply%20file%20for%20bankruptcy%20at%20the%20federal%20level%20to%20ensure%20the%20CFB%20could%20not%20come%20after%20her.%26quot%3B%20(A%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20CFB%2C%20Tim%20Hunter%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20whether%20the%20board%20opened%20an%20investigation.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20instinct%20may%20have%20presaged%20what%20came%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221636%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20New%20York%20City%20Campaign%20Finance%20Board%20contact%20record%20dated%20February%2010%2C%202022%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64df85e0b698ac0019dc4e59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22618%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20Tirschwell's%20failed%202021%20bid%20for%20New%20York%20City%20mayor%2C%20a%20Campaign%20Finance%20Board%20staffer%20contacted%20her%20with%20questions.%20The%20staffer's%20writeup%20from%20February%2010%2C%202022%2C%20notes%20Tirschwell%20saying%20if%20the%20board%20came%20after%20her%2C%20she'd%20file%20for%20bankruptcy.%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20City%20Campaign%20Finance%20Board%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20six%20months%20after%20Tirschwell%20dropped%20out%20of%20the%20race%2C%20she%20sold%20her%20Manhattan%20condo%20for%20%242.6%20million%2C%20rented%20an%20apartment%20on%20the%2029th%20floor%20of%20a%20high-rise%20building%20in%20Houston%2C%20and%20embarked%20on%20another%20adventure%20in%20bankruptcy%2C%20Corizon's%20Texas%20Two-Step.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20apartment%20was%20more%20than%20her%20personal%20residence%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919692-yescare-corp-certificate-of-formation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIncorporation%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20that%20Tirschwell%20listed%20her%20apartment%20as%20the%20business%20address%20for%20YesCare%20Corp.%2C%20the%20company%20that%20owns%20YesCare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20her%20short%20tenure%20at%20Corizon%2C%20and%20then%20YesCare%2C%20Tirschwell%20bid%20for%20new%20business%2C%20including%20in%20Alabama%2C%20and%20reached%20out%20to%20corrections%20officials%20to%20reassure%20them%20about%20the%20transfer%20of%20ownership.%20Bryan%20Baker%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20New%20Mexico%20jail%20where%20Hector%20Garcia's%20health%20catastrophically%20collapsed%2C%20recalled%20an%20in-person%20visit%20Tirschwell%20made%20to%20the%20facility%2C%20some%20three%20years%20after%20Garcia%20died%2C%20where%20they%20briefly%20discussed%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20seems%20clear%20in%20retrospect%20that%20Tirschwell%20was%20brought%20on%20to%20accomplish%20one%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankruptcy%20was%20in%20Tirschwell's%20playbook.%20Her%20Quest%20profile%20says%20she%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20a%20guest%20lecturer%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20bankruptcy%20investing.%26quot%3B%20Back%20in%202004%2C%20after%20many%20companies%20with%20asbestos%20tort%20liabilities%20had%20been%20driven%20into%20bankruptcy%2C%20she%20joined%20with%20other%20hedge%20funds%20in%20meeting%20with%20members%20of%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee%20to%20discuss%20the%20idea%20of%20establishing%20a%20trust%20fund%20to%20pay%20those%20claims.%20A%20decade%20later%2C%20companies%20with%20asbestos%20claims%20were%20the%20first%20to%20deploy%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20the%20only%20Corizon%20leader%20based%20in%20Texas%2C%20where%20the%20Two-Step%20is%20legal%2C%20and%20the%20timeline%20suggests%20she%20may%20have%20been%20brought%20on%20specifically%20to%20oversee%20the%20company's%20legal%20maneuvers%20in%20Texas.%20She%20was%20referred%20to%20as%20part%20of%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Btransitional%20leadership%20team%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919669-st-clair-county-michigan-emails%23document%2Fp1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFebruary%20email%3C%2Fa%3E%20sent%20from%20a%20YesCare%20administrator%20to%20a%20county%20agency%20in%20Michigan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20days%20after%20the%20bankruptcy%2C%20Tirschwell%20was%20out%20the%20door%2C%20with%20Corizon's%20long-standing%20CFO%20Jeff%20Sholey%20taking%20the%20company's%20reins.%20Sholey%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20detailed%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20she%20was%20CEO%20for%20just%2015%20months%2C%20she%20was%20rewarded%20with%20a%205%25%20ownership%20stake%20in%20YesCare%20Corp.%20Despite%20the%20bankruptcy%2C%20Tirschwell%20writes%20of%20YesCare%20on%20her%20LinkedIn%20page%20that%20she%20executed%20the%20%26quot%3Bsuccessful%20turnaround%20of%20a%2045%20year%20old%20correctional%20healthcare%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteven%20Storch%2C%20Tirschwell's%20attorney%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20her%20behalf%2C%20citing%20pending%20litigation%2C%20and%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20detailed%20follow-up%20questions.%20But%20he%20said%20she%20%26quot%3Bhas%20long%20been%20a%20passionate%20advocate%20for%20improvements%20to%20the%20prison%20healthcare%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222138%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Medical%20hallway%20lit%20by%20fluorescent%20lights.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64df7b2cbd98a60019790786%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221604%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20hallway%20inside%20the%20Do%C3%B1a%20Ana%20County%20Detention%20Center.%3Cp%3EAdria%20Malcom%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20an%20Insider%20reporter%20stopped%20by%20the%20Do%C3%B1a%20Ana%20County%20Detention%20Center%2C%20the%20low-slung%20facility%20in%20Las%20Cruces%2C%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20Chihuahuan%20Desert%2C%20that%20Tirschwell%20had%20visited%20a%20year%20before%20%E2%80%94%20the%20place%20where%20Hector%20Garcia%20spent%20his%20final%20days.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20facility's%20nursing%20station%2C%20where%20Garcia's%20family%20said%20in%20a%20civil%20complaint%20that%20he'd%20received%20%26quot%3Binadequate%20medical%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20YesCare%20and%20Corizon%20posters%20are%20now%20plastered%20side-by-side.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hallway's%20fluorescent%20lights%20added%20a%20harshness%20to%20the%20already%20desolate%20environment.%20The%20prison%20gave%20off%20a%20musty%2C%20almost%20putrid%20smell%20and%20in%20the%20cells%2C%20men%20lay%20on%20their%20metal%20bunks%2C%20turned%20to%20the%20wall.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20facility%20is%20where%20Garcia%20collapsed%20just%20three%20days%20into%20his%20six-day%20sentence%3B%20where%20a%20corrections%20officer%20found%20him%20crawling%20on%20the%20floor%20and%20moaning%3B%20where%20a%20nurse%20practitioner%20from%20Corizon%20responded%20to%20his%20severe%20pain%2C%20distended%20abdomen%2C%20and%20his%20vomiting%20of%20dark%20brown%20bile%20by%20putting%20him%20in%20a%20medical%20observation%20cell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20family's%20lawsuit%2C%20emergency%20rooms%20frequently%20encounter%20perforated%20ulcers%20and%20a%20routine%20surgery%20can%20treat%20the%20condition.%20Left%20untreated%2C%20however%2C%20the%20condition%20can%20be%20fatal.%20Time%20matters%2C%20and%20Corizon%20staffers%20waited%20until%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20on%20August%206%20%E2%80%94%20two%20days%20after%20the%20onset%20of%20Garcia's%20symptoms%20%E2%80%94%20to%20send%20him%20to%20the%20hospital.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222223%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Family%20picture%20resting%20against%20a%20window.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64df7ba6b698ac0019dc3a67%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20photo%20of%20Hector%20Garcia%20with%20his%20family%20sits%20by%20a%20window%20at%20his%20son%20Daniel's%20house%20in%20Las%20Cruces.%3Cp%3EAdria%20Malcom%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EHe%20was%20already%20unconscious%20by%20the%20time%20his%20family%20arrived%20at%20his%20bedside%2C%20after%20his%20sister%20received%20a%20call%20from%20a%20nurse%20at%20the%20hospital.%20To%20this%20day%2C%20no%20one%20from%20the%20detention%20facility%20or%20from%20Corizon%20has%20sent%20condolences%20to%20the%20family%2C%20or%20contacted%20them%20at%20all.%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20can%20our%20system%20allow%20this%20to%20people%3F%26quot%3B%20Hector%20Garcia%20Jr.%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20he%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20call%20an%20ambulance%20himself.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Garcias%20may%20never%20get%20a%20chance%20to%20make%20the%20case%20that%20his%20death%20could%20have%20been%20prevented.%20If%20Tehum's%20owners%20get%20their%20way%20during%20the%20settlement%20negotiations%20scheduled%20for%20this%20week%2C%20they%20could%20skirt%20accountability%20not%20just%20for%20Hector%20Garcia's%20death%2C%20but%20for%20the%20for%20hundreds%20of%20vulnerable%20prisoners%20who%20say%20they%20experienced%20serious%20harm%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20a%20company%20paid%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20keep%20them%20safe.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20project%20was%20completed%20with%20the%20support%20of%20a%20grant%20from%20Columbia%20University's%20Ira%20A.%20Lipman%20Center%20for%20Journalism%20and%20Civil%20and%20Human%20Rights%20in%20conjunction%20with%20Arnold%20Ventures.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ch2%3ECredits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cspan%3EReporters%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENicole%20Einbinder%2C%20Dakin%20Campbell%2C%20Katherine%20Long%2C%20Jack%20Newsham%2C%20Hannah%20Beckler%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cspan%3EEditors%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EEsther%20Kaplan%2C%20Jeffrey%20Cane%2C%20John%20Cook%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cspan%3EVisuals%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EKazi%20Awal%2C%20Isabel%20Fernandez-Pujol%2C%20Annie%20Fu%2C%20Rebecca%20Zisser%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cspan%3EVideo%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EErica%20Domena%2C%20