riefing%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20on%20the%20visit%20of%20the%20Indian%20PM.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20a%20positive%20intent%20and%20an%20open%20mind%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20BRICS%20expansion%2C%E2%80%9D%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Mohan%20Kwatra%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20admitted%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cconsiderable%20among%20many%20countries%20to%20become%20part%20of%20BRICS%2C%20to%20associate%20with%20BRICS%2C%20to%20leverage%20the%20opportunities%20with%20BRICS%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKwatra%20noted%20that%20the%20modalities%20for%20the%20inclusion%20of%20new%20members%20into%20the%20BRICS%20are%20being%20discussed%20among%20the%20Sherpas%20of%20the%20grouping.%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20not%20want%20to%20prejudge%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20discussions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20UK%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20an%20unnamed%20Chinese%20official%20as%20saying%20that%20an%20expanded%20G7%20could%20balance%20out%20the%20group%20of%20developed%20nations.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20expand%20Brics%20to%20account%20for%20a%20similar%20portion%20of%20world%20GDP%20as%20the%20G7%2C%20then%20our%20collective%20voice%20in%20the%20world%20will%20grow%20stronger%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Chinese%20official%20told%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20article%20in%20the%20state-run%20%3Cem%3EPeople%E2%80%99s%20Daily%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fpaper.people.com.cn%2Frmrb%2Fhtml%2F2023-08%2F21%2Fnw.D110000renmrb_20230821_3-02.htm%5C%22%3EChinese%20ambassador%20to%20South%20Africa%20Chen%20Xiadong%3C%2Fa%3E%20batted%20for%20the%20expansion%20of%20BRICS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLast%20year%2C%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20pointed%20out%20at%20the%2014th%20BRICS%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Meeting%20that%20the%20BRICS%20countries%20are%20not%20closed%20clubs%20or%20exclusive%20%E2%80%98cliques%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20a%20big%20family%20of%20mutual%20support%20and%20good%20partners%20for%20win-win%20cooperation.%20During%20the%20meeting%2C%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20five%20countries%20reached%20an%20important%20consensus%20on%20the%20expansion%20of%20BRICS%20and%20supported%20the%20discussion%20of%20standards%20and%20procedures%20for%20expansion.%20China%20welcomes%20and%20looks%20forward%20to%20like-minded%20partners%20joining%20the%20BRICS%20family%20at%20an%20early%20date%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20would%20be%20travelling%20to%20South%20Africa%2C%20along%20with%20Brazilian%20President%20Luiz%20In%C3%A1cio%20Lula%20da%20Silva%20who%20had%20recently%20expressed%20his%20support%20to%20bringing%20Argentina%2C%20Venezuela%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20into%20the%20fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20queried%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20BRICS%20adopting%20a%20common%20currency%2C%20the%20foreign%20secretary%20explained%20that%20there%20exist%20several%20essential%20conditions%20that%20must%20be%20met%20before%20implementing%20such%20a%20unified%20currency%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20senior%20Indian%20diplomat%20was%20circumspect%20on%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20Indian%20PM%20meeting%20with%20President%20Xi%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20I%20would%20say%20that%20the%20host%20country%20has%20invited%20a%20large%20number%20of%20guest%20countries.%20The%20PM%E2%80%99s%20schedule%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%20with%20those%20present%20in%20South%20Africa%20is%20still%20being%20worked%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20several%20indications%20that%20India%20has%20been%20keen%20to%20have%20a%20meeting%20between%20Modi%20and%20Xi%20in%20Johannesburg.%20A%20short%20encounter%20was%20assured%20when%20Xi%20comes%20to%20Delhi%20for%20the%20G-20%20summit%20as%20part%20of%20protoc