eg-injury-after-being-crushed-by-tractor-trolley%25C2%25A0%5C%22%3Egot%20squeezed%20between%20tractor%20trolley%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20the%20police%20tried%20to%20stop%20the%20protesting%20farmers%2C%20according%20to%20the%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20farmer%20leaders%20from%20Haryana%20and%20Punjab%20were%20detained%20by%20respective%20state%20police%20ahead%20of%20a%20protest%20in%20Chandigarh%20to%20seek%20compensation%20for%20losses%20caused%20by%20recent%20floods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2020%20people%20from%20Haryana%20and%2050%20from%20Punjab%20have%20been%20detained%20from%20various%20districts%20ahead%20of%20the%20protest%20on%20August%2022%20in%20Chandigarh%2C%20sources%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20witnessed%20flooding%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20terrible%20financial%20losses%20to%20farmers.%20Since%20then%2C%20farmers%E2%80%99%20bodies%20have%20been%20demanding%20compensation%20for%20flood%20victims.%20They%20are%20seeking%20compensation%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%20per%20acre%20for%20crop%20loss%2C%20Rs%205%20lakh%20for%20a%20damaged%20house%2C%20and%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20compensation%20for%20a%20family%20of%20a%20deceased%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmer%20leaders%20expressed%20their%20dissatisfaction%20with%20both%20the%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20state%20governments%20for%20not%20providing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh-news%2Ffarmers-to-gherao-chandigarh-on-august-22-demand-compensation-for-flood-losses-101692475927584.html%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cconcrete%20response%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20compensation%20for%20flood%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Location%20of%20detained%20farm%20leader%20unknown%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20ones%20arrested%20was%20Amarjeet%20Singh%20Morhi%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20Bhartiya%20Kisan%20Union%20%E2%80%93%20Shaheed%20Bhagat%20Singh%20(BKU%20SBS).%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20with%20Tejveer%20Singh%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20of%20BKU%20SBS.%20Singh%20said%20that%20Morhi%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20asked%20to%20arrive%20at%20the%20Ambala%20police%20station%20by%20the%20Superintendent%20of%20Police.%20Since%20then%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20where%20the%20police%20have%20taken%20our%20chief%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20light%20of%20the%20protest%20on%20Tuesday%2C%2016%20farmer%20organisations%20had%20met%20at%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Director%20General%20of%20Police%20(DGP)%2C%20Chandigarh%20on%20Sunday.%20The%20DGPs%20of%20Haryana%20and%20Punjab%20along%20with%20CID%20and%20Intelligence%20officers%20from%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20were%20also%20present%20during%20the%20meeting.%20Notably%2C%20the%20detained%20leader%20%E2%80%93%20Amarjeet%20Singh%20Morhi%20%E2%80%93%20of%20the%20BKU%20SBS%20was%20also%20present%20during%20the%20meeting%20at%20the%20DGP%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20protest%20for%20August%2022%20was%20for%20the%20compensation%20of%20flood%20victims.%20Other%20than%20that%2C%20we%20had%20demands%20regarding%20increasing%20the%20work%20under%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%2C%20(MGNREGA).%20Also%2C%20in%20Chandigarh%2C%20several%20criminal%20cases%20from%20the%20Farmers%20Protest%20days%20haven%E2%80%99t%20been%20withdrawn.%20We%20wanted%20to%20protest%20in%20Chandigarh%20regarding%20these%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98AAP-BJP%20working%20together%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20farmer%20leaders%20were%20detained%20on%20Monday%2C%20Singh%20alleged%20that%20the%20arrests%20were%20a%20work%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cjoint%20operation%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20BJP%20government%20of%20Haryana%20and%20the%20AAP%20government%20of%20Punjab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20never%20conducted%20a%20joint%20operation%20to%20stop%20drugs%2C%20neither%20did%20they%20conduct%20one%20to%20stop%20communal%20violence%2C%20but%20both%20the%20states%20came%20together%20to%20stop%20a%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protest%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20spokesperson%20of%20BKU%20SBS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20crackdown%2C%20farmer%20groups%20are%20adamant%20on%20protesting%20for%20the%20compensation%20of%20flood%20victims%20on%20August%2022%20in%20Chandigarh.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692630110000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21202203%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-21-at-6.22.15-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpunjab-farmer-dies-after-police-resorts-to-lathi-charge-during-protest-for-flood-victims%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Several%20farmers%20who%20have%20been%20marching%20to%20Chandigarh%20from%20various%20parts%20of%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20to%20hold%20a%20protest%20demonstration%20on%20August%2022%20have%20been%20detained.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpunjab-farmer-dies-after-police-resorts-to-lathi-charge-during-protest-for-flood-victims%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22850%20still%20missing%20after%20Maui%20fires%2C%20mayor%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692628630000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F170D0%2Fproduction%2F_130861449_e212bc4b599f5672fcca34051fa7790fe9d0a5450_43_5000_28121000x563.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66571294%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20expected%20to%20visit%20the%20island%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20deadly%20wildfires.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A208%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66571294%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66571294.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66571294.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Union%20Home%20Ministry%20Tops%20Corruption%20Complaints%2C%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Report%20Finds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F21165755%2FHome-Ministry-PTI9_19_2019_000103B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20(CVC)%2C%20in%20its%20annual%20report%2C%20has%20said%20that%20it%20has%20received%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20corruption%20complaints%20relating%20to%20officers%20and%20employees%20of%20the%20Union%20ministry%20for%20home%20affairs%20(MHA)%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20it%20had%20received%20a%20total%20of%201%2C15%2C203%20complaints%20till%20December%2031%2C%202022%2C%20across%20all%20departments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%2085%2C437%20complaints%20had%20been%20disposed%2C%2029%2C766%20were%20pending%2C%20and%2022%2C034%20were%20pending%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20highest%20number%20of%20complaints%20related%20to%20MHA%20(46%2C643)%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20Railways%20(10%2C580)%20and%20Banks%20(8%2C129).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CVC%20is%20the%20apex%20agency%20overseeing%20and%20supervising%20the%20vigilance%20administration%20of%20the%20organisations%20owned%20or%20controlled%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20covered%20under%20the%20advisory%20jurisdiction%20of%20the%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20meant%20to%20tackle%20corruption%20and%20make%20the%20administrative%20system%20transparent%20and%20objective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHighest%20corruption%20complaints%20in%20MHA%2C%20Railways%2C%20and%20Banking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20of%20the%2046%2C643%20complaints%20received%20against%20officers%20and%20employees%20of%20the%20MHA%2C%2023%2C919%20were%20disposed%20of%3B%2022%2C724%20were%20pending%20and%2019%2C198%20were%20pending%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20of%20the%2010%2C580%20complaints%20it%20had%20received%20relating%20to%20Railways%2C%209%2C663%20were%20disposed%20of%2C%20917%20were%20pending%20and%20nine%20were%20pending%20for%20over%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%208%2C129%20complaints%20against%20employees%20and%20officers%20of%20Banks%2C%207%2C762%20were%20disposed%20of%2C%20367%20were%20pending%20and%2078%20were%20pending%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20there%20were%207%2C370%20complaints%20against%20employees%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%2C%206%2C804%20were%20disposed%20of%20and%20566%20were%20pending%2C%20including%2018%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeviations%20from%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20there%20were%2027%20cases%20of%20deviation%20from%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%20across%2016%20departments%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20included-Ministry%20of%20Railways%20(7)%2C%20Bharat%20Sanchar%20Nigam%20Ltd%20(1)%2C%20V.O%20Chidambaranar%20Port%20Authority%20(1)%2C%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(2)%2C%20New%20India%20Assurance%20Company%20Ltd%20(1)%2C%20Industrial%20Development%20Bank%20of%20India%20(1)%2C%20Small%20Industries%20Development%20Bank%20of%20India%20(1)%2C%20Bharat%20Coking%20Coal%20Ltd%20(1)%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Coal%20(2)%2C%20Nuclear%20Power%20Corporation%20of%20India%20Ltd%20(2)%2C%20Bird%20Group%20of%20Companies%20(1)%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Textiles%20(1)%2C%20NBCC%20(India)%20Ltd%20(3)%2C%20Delhi%20State%20Industrial%20and%20Infrastructure%20Development%20Corporation%20(1)%2C%20Delhi%20Jal%20Board%20(1)%2C%20and%20Delhi%20Transco%20Ltd%20(1).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhenever%20the%20Ministry%2FDepartment%20proposes%20to%20differ%20from%20or%20not%20to%20accept%20any%20advice%20of%20the%20Commission%2C%20a%20procedure%20has%20been%20laid%20down%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20%26amp%3B%20Administrative%20Reforms%2C%20which%20prescribes%20that%20in%20those%20cases%20of%20officers%20for%20whom%20the%20Appointing%20Authority%20is%20the%20President%2C%20(orders%20are%20required%20to%20be%20issued%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20President)%2C%20a%20reference%20is%20to%20be%20made%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20%26amp%3B%20Training%20(DOPT)%20before%20the%20Ministry%2FDepartment%20finally%20decides%20such%20cases%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNon-acceptance%20of%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%20vitiates%20the%20vigilance%20process%20and%20weakens%20the%20impartiality%20of%20the%20vigilance%20administration.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20cases%20of%20deviation%20from%20a%20prescribed%20procedure%20or%20non-acceptance%20of%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20major%20instances%20of%20deviation%20cases%20from%20the%20CVC%E2%80%99s%20advice%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinistry%20of%20Railways%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20working%20as%20chief%20workshop%20manager%20(CWM)%2C%20an%20officer%20was%20found%20responsible%20for%20committing%20gross%20misconduct%20by%20introducing%20the%20then%20(senior%20section%20engineer%20(SSE))%20as%20his%20friend%20to%20the%20supplier%20and%20demanding%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2025%2C000%20through%20the%20then%20SSE%20for%20passing%20the%20supplier%E2%80%99s%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20CVC%20had%20advised%20imposition%20of%20a%20major%20penalty%20in%20the%20case%2C%20the%20Railway%20Board%20decided%20to%20exonerate%20him%20which%20the%20commission%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmajor%20deviation%E2%80%9D%20from%20its%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20instance%2C%20another%20senior%20section%20engineer%20was%20found%20responsible%20for%20processing%20payment%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20fake%20inspection%20certificate.%20The%20officer%20was%20also%20exonerated%20in%20a%20deviation%20from%20the%20CVC%E2%80%99s%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20instance%2C%20a%20senior%20divisional%20engineer%20failed%20to%20investigate%20complaints%20received%20from%20an%20additional%20divisional%20railway%20manager%20(ADRM)%20and%20failed%20to%20exercise%20due%20diligence%20in%20the%20scrutiny%20of%20credential%20documents%20of%20a%20firm.%20This%20resulted%20in%20award%20of%20contract%20to%20a%20firm%20on%20fake%2Fforged%20credential%20papers.%20While%20the%20Commission%20adviced%20major%20penalty%2C%20only%20a%20minor%20penalty%20was%20imposed%20by%20the%20Railway%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelhi%20Jal%20Board%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIrregularities%20were%20found%20in%20the%20tendering%20process%20for%20the%20award%20of%20work%20of%20construction%20of%2050-kilo%20litres%20per%20day%20sewage%20treatment%20plant%20(STP)%20and%20other%20associated%20works%20on%20a%20Design-Build%20Operate%20basis%20at%20Raj%20Niwas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Commission%20had%20advised%20imposing%20a%20major%20penalty%2C%20the%20Disciplinary%20Authority%20exonerated%20the%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinistry%20of%20Textile%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAn%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Fashion%20Technology%20(NIFT)%20Bhubaneshwar%20was%20found%20responsible%20for%20gross%20violation%20in%20tender%20evaluation%20and%20for%20proposing%20to%20release%20part%20payment%20directly%20to%20the%20individual%20and%20not%20to%20the%20firm%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20work%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20major%20penalty%20was%20imposed%20by%20the%20Disciplinary%20Authority%2C%20the%20Appellate%20Authority%20later%20exonerated%20the%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinistry%20of%20Coal%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEastern%20Coalfields%20Ltd%20(ECL)%20awarded%20contracts%20for%20hiring%20Heavy%20Earth%20Moving%20Machinery%20(HEMM)%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20overburden%2C%20extraction%2C%20and%20removal%20of%20coal%20from%20Mohanpur%2C%20OCP%20patch%20of%20Salanpur%20Area%20and%20Jambad%20Open%20Cast%20Project%20(OCP)%20Kajora%20Area.%20The%20contracts%20were%20foreclosed%20and%20were%20awarded%20at%20higher%20rates%20in%20retendering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20two%20officers%20were%20exonerated%20in%20a%20major%20deviation%20from%20its%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajor%2C%20minor%20penalties%20and%20exonerations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20annual%20reports%20of%20chief%20vigilance%20officers%20(CVOs)%20of%20organisations%20%E2%80%93%20major%20penalty%20proceedings%20were%20initiated%20in%206%2C501%20cases%20for%20all%20categories%20of%20officers%20dealt%20with%20by%20the%20CVO.%20This%20resulted%20in%20the%20imposition%20of%20major%20penalties%20in%205%2C298%20cases%20and%20minor%20penalties%20or%20warnings%20in%20552%20cases.%20651%20cases%20resulted%20in%20exoneration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinor%20penalty%20proceedings%20were%20initiated%20in%2013%2C661%20cases%20in%20which%20minor%20penalties%20or%20warnings%20were%20issued%20in%2011%2C751%20cases%20and%203%2C752%20cases%20were%20exonerated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%202022%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20of%20the%20total%201%2C849%20departmental%20inquiries%20under%20process%2C%20880%20were%20completed%20and%20969%20were%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20some%20of%20the%20major%20organisations%20that%20took%20disciplinary%20action%20against%20officials%20conducting%20misconduct%20including%20penalties%20and%20administrative%20action%20include%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(346)%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Railways%20(142)%2C%20Central%20Board%20of%20Indirect%20Taxes%20and%20Customs%20(88)%2C%20Employees%20Provident%20Fund%20Organisation%20(85)%2C%20Indian%20Oil%20Corporation%20Ltd%20(79)%2C%20Union%20Bank%20of%20India%20(68)%2C%20Bharat%20Coking%20Coal%20Ltd%20(64).%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692627615000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F21165755%2FHome-Ministry-PTI9_19_2019_000103B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Funion-home-ministry-tops-corruption-complaints-central-vigilance-commission-report-finds%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20CVC's%202022%20annual%20report%2C%20it%20had%20received%20a%20total%20of%201%2C15%2C203%20complaints%20across%20all%20departments.%20The%20highest%20number%20of%20complaints%20were%20received%20against%20Union%20home%20ministry%20(46%2C643)%2C%20Railways%20(10%2C580)%2C%20and%20Banks%20(8%2C129).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Funion-home-ministry-tops-corruption-complaints-central-vigilance-commission-report-finds%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%8BSequels%20that%20were%20loved%20as%20much%20as%20original%E2%80%8B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692627300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102912811%2Cimgsize-60330.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Fsequels-which-were-loved-as-much-as-the-original%2Fphotostory%2F102912811.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102912811.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%E2%80%8BSequels%20which%20were%20loved%20as%20much%20as%20the%20original%E2%80%8B%2