20in%20Britain%2C%20where%20the%20prospect%20of%20nationalisation%20was%20seen%20as%20potentially%20hugely%20damaging%20to%20the%20economy.%20Furthermore%2C%20it%20would%20have%20undermined%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20influence%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Plotting%20to%20depose%20Mosaddegh%20began%20in%20earnest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20event%2C%20the%20coup%20%E2%80%93%20named%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2017%2F06%2F20%2F64-years-later-cia-finally-releases-details-of-iranian-coup-iran-tehran-oil%2F%5C%22%3EOperation%20Ajax%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20was%20a%20joint%20venture%20between%20the%20CIA%20and%20MI6.%20The%20shah%2C%20Mohammad%20Reza%20Pahlavi%2C%20who%20had%20recently%20fled%20the%20country%20after%20an%20earlier%20plot%20to%20remove%20Mossadegh%20had%20failed%2C%20returned%20to%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20short%20period%2C%20he%20had%20tightened%20his%20grip%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20security%20services%20and%20imposed%20a%20dictatorial%20regime%20which%20ruled%20through%20brutality%20and%20fear.%20Pahlavi%20banned%20all%20opposition%20political%20parties%2C%20and%20many%20of%20the%20activists%20who%20participated%20in%20the%20movement%20for%20nationalisation%20of%20oil%20were%20arrested%20or%20fled%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%20by%20fear%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201957%2C%20the%20shah%20established%20an%20internal%20security%20service%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FSAVAK%5C%22%3ESazman-e%20Ettel%E2%80%99at%20va%20Amniyat-e%20Keshvar%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Savak)%2C%20which%20essentially%20ran%20Iran%20at%20the%20shah%E2%80%99s%20bidding.%20From%20then%20until%201975%2C%20only%20two%20major%20political%20parties%20were%20allowed%20to%20operate%2C%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20(%3Cem%3E%E1%B8%A4ezb-e%20Mardom%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20the%20New%20Iran%20Party%20(%3Cem%3E%E1%B8%A4ezb-e%20Iran-e%20Novin%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20and%