Focus%20During%20the%20BRICS%20Summit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21155630%2FNDB-HQ-LOGO.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20%E2%80%98BRICS%E2%80%99%20meet%20has%20possibly%20attracted%20as%20much%20global%20attention%20as%20the%2015th%20summit%2C%20which%20is%20to%20be%20hosted%20by%20South%20Africa%20in%20Johannesburg%20from%20%60August%2022%20to%2024.%20South%20Africa%20was%20under%20heavy%20domestic%20and%20international%20pressure%20not%20to%20host%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20for%20the%20summit.%20Pretoria%20was%20saved%20from%20a%20diplomatic%20predicament%20when%20it%20announced%20on%20July%2019%20that%20Putin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fputin-wont-attend-brics-summit-in-south-africa-owing-to-icc-arrest-warrant%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dworld-%2CPutin%2520Won%2527t%2520Attend%2520BRICS%2520Summit%2520in%2520South%2520Africa%2520Owing%2Cto%2520land%2520in%2520South%2520Africa.%5C%22%3Ewould%20not%20attend%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Summit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20British%20economist%20James%20O%E2%80%99Neill%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goldmansachs.com%2Fintelligence%2Farchive%2Fbuilding-better.html%5C%22%3Ecoined%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20acronym%20%E2%80%98BRIC%E2%80%99%20for%20countries%20he%20identified%20as%20being%20at%20a%20similar%20stage%20of%20newly%20advanced%20economic%20development%2C%20he%20argued%20that%20global%20governance%20was%20not%20optimal%20anymore%20and%20there%20was%20a%20need%20to%20change%20the%20structure%20to%20give%20big%20emerging%20countries%20more%20power.%20Eight%20years%20later%2C%20the%20leaders%20of%20those%20four%20held%20their%20first%20summit%2C%20turning%20an%20economist%E2%80%99s%20thoughts%20into%20a%20global%20organisation%2C%20incorporating%20South%20Africa%20a%20year%20later.%20Twenty-two%20years%20since%20that%20articulation%2C%20and%20fourteen%20years%20since%20its%20formation%2C%20BRICS%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20significant%20grouping%20with%20a%20growing%20clout%20in%20global%20economic%20governance.%20Accounting%20for%2031.5%25%20of%20global%20GDP%2C%20the%20five%20BRICS%20nations%20%E2%80%93%20Brazil%2C%20Russia%2C%20India%2C%20China%20and%20South%20Africa%20%E2%80%93%20together%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.silkroadbriefing.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2F27%2Fthe-brics-has-overtaken-the-g7-in-global-gdp%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520current%2520BRICS%2520five%2520now%2Calmost%2520certainly%2520bringing%2520that%2520forward.%5C%22%3Esupersede%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20GDP%20contribution%20of%20the%20G7%20nations%20which%20stands%20at%2030.7%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20post-pandemic%20world%2C%20with%20an%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20expanding%20Western%20economic%20sanctions%2C%20heightened%20antagonisms%20between%20US%20and%20China%2C%20geopolitical%20tensions%20with%20Russia%2C%20SWIFT%20restrictions%2C%20collaring%20at%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20various%20bodies%2C%20suspension%20from%20Financial%20Action%20Task%20Force%20(FATF)%2C%20policy%20debates%20around%20alternatives%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreservehistory.org%2Fessays%2Fbretton-woods-created%5C%22%3EBretton%20Woods%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20heated%20up.%20As%20targeted%20countries%20begin%20exploring%20the%20possibility%20of%20settling%20international%20payments%20in%20local%20currencies%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20BRICS%20forum%20leading%20the%20way%20is%20being%20debated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F24133623%2Fpexels-pratikxox-4025825.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F24133623%2Fpexels-pratikxox-4025825.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F24133623%2Fpexels-pratikxox-4025825-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F24133623%2Fpexels-pratikxox-4025825-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-654606%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20currency%20notes.%20Photo%3A%20Pratikxox%2FPexels%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDiscussions%20around%20new%20members%2C%20new%20governance%20and%20new%20currency%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20New%20Development%20Bank%20(NDB%2C%20sometimes%20called%20the%20BRICS%20Bank)%20has%20arguably%20been%20the%20one%20concrete%20success%20for%20the%20BRICS%20political%20grouping.%20The%20NDB%20was%20established%20to%20promote%20the%20financing%20of%20infrastructure%20projects%20among%20developing%20countries%2C%20has%20expanded%2C%20and%20finds%20itself%20placed%20to%20challenge%20existing%20multilateral%20development%20institutions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NDB%E2%80%99s%20mandate%20is%20to%20mobilise%20resources%20for%20infrastructure%20and%20sustainable%20development%20projects.%20Time%20and%20again%2C%20the%20five-member%20nations%20have%20agreed%20to%20extend%20credit%20facilities%20in%20local%20currency%20to%20each%20other.%20But%20this%20has%20not%20been%20so%20easy%20given%20that%20the%20US%20dollar%20is%20the%20current%20base%20currency%20in%20global%20trade.%20Financing%20of%20the%20NDB%20comes%20from%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20major%20developing%20economies.%20This%20translates%20into%20financing%20from%20one%20developing%20country%20to%20another%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20New%20South-South%20cooperation.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20the%20capacity%20of%20the%20new%20Development%20Bank%20has%20been%20enhanced%20since%20its%20inception.%20But%20whether%20the%20NDB%20will%20undertake%20sensitive%20and%20complex%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20the%20future%20is%20the%20key%20question.%20The%20other%20is%20what%20amount%20of%20financing%20can%20NDB%20make%20available.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20first%20benchmark%20issuance%20since%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%2C%20the%20NDB%2C%20issued%20a%20US%20%241.25%20billion%2C%20three-year%20green%20bond%2C%20in%20April%20with%20a%20%E2%80%98use%20of%20proceeds%E2%80%99%20clause%20stipulating%20that%20any%20funds%20raised%20will%20not%20be%20used%20to%20invest%20in%20Russia%2C%20that%20attracted%20investors%20from%20diverse%20jurisdictions%2C%20not%20just%20the%20BRICS%20members%20and%20NDB%20members%20Bangladesh%2C%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Uruguay.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20and%20the%20imposition%20of%20wide%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%2C%20none%20of%20the%20other%20four%20BRICS%20nations%20participated%20in%20the%20economic%20sanctions%20against%20Russia.%20However%2C%20the%20BRICS%20bank%20announced%20that%20it%20has%20put%20new%20transactions%20in%20Russia%20on%20hold.%20Post%20Crimea-2014%20too%2C%20the%20BRICS%20Bank%20found%20it%20difficult%20to%20lend%20money%20for%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20infrastructure%20projects.%20Posting%20on%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20X%2C%20Dilma%20Rousseff%2C%20President%20of%20BRICS%20NDB%2C%20has%20put%20to%20rest%20speculations%20concerning%20the%20discussion%20of%20new%20operations%20of%20the%20bank%20in%20Russia%20were%20%E2%80%9Cunfounded.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20line%20with%20restrictions%20imposed%20in%20financial%20and%20capital%20markets%2C%20the%20NDB%20is%20not%20considering%20new%20projects%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFitch%20has%20in%20the%20past%20affirmed%20NDB%20ratings%20at%20%E2%80%98AA%2B%E2%80%99%20because%20of%20its%20strong%20credit%20fundamentals%2C%20including%20its%20large%20capital%20buffers.%20In%202020%2C%20it%20revised%20the%20outlook%20on%20NDB%E2%80%99s%20Long-Term%20Issuer%20Default%20Rating%20(IDR)%20to%20%E2%80%98Negative%E2%80%99%20from%20%E2%80%98Stable%E2%80%99%20because%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20presence%20and%20role%20of%20Russia%20as%20a%20large%20shareholder%E2%80%9D%3B%20but%20in%20its%20recent%20Outlook%20on%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fitchratings.com%2Fresearch%2Fsovereigns%2Ffitch-revises-outlook-on-new-development-bank-to-negative-affirms-at-aa-17-03-2022%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENDB%E2%80%99s%20IDR%20has%20been%20revised%20back%20to%20%E2%80%98Stable%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20an%20overall%20assessment%20of%20its%20business%20environment%20as%20%E2%80%98medium%20risk%E2%80%99.%20The%20assessment%20is%20that%20the%20NDB%20has%20succeeded%20in%20continuing%20to%20grow%20its%20balance%20sheet%20and%20attract%20new%20shareholders%2C%20despite%20the%20negative%20impact%20that%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20has%20had%20on%20its%20operations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20has%20been%20speculation%20about%20a%20new%2C%20gold-backed%20currency.%20But%20debates%20around%20de-dollarisation%20are%20not%20new%20and%20in%20the%20past%20also%20BRICS%20has%20flirted%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20global%20reserve%20currency.%20A%20new%20currency%20would%20require%20extensive%20negotiation%20and%20the%20establishment%20of%20mechanisms%20for%20exchange%20rates%2C%20payment%20systems%2C%20and%20financial%20market%20regulation.%20The%20key%20focus%20at%20the%20upcoming%20BRICS%20summit%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20discussion%20relating%20to%20a%20long-term%20integrated%20payment%20system%20for%20cross-border%20commerce.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWider%2C%20state-led%20geostrategy%20to%20bypass%20the%20dollar%20is%20now%20a%20reality.%20Even%20though%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20cooperation%20among%20the%20developing%20nations%20is%20not%20taking%20place%20via%20the%20mechanism%20of%20BRICS%2C%20the%20war%20itself%20has%20forced%20emerging%20economies%20to%20seek%20alternatives%20to%20the%20Bretton%20Woods%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20ramifications%20does%20expansion%20have%20for%20BRICS%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20as%20many%20as%2023%20nations%20expressing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fbrics-open-to-expansion-gives-call-for-a-multipolar-world%5C%22%3Edesire%20to%20join%20the%20grouping%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20BRICS%20expansion%20is%20an%20aspect%20that%20has%20attracted%20a%20lot%20of%20media%20attention.%20Notwithstanding%20its%20current%20slowdown%2C%20China%20is%20today%20the%20second-largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%20and%20first%20on%20a%20purchasing%20power%20parity%20(PPP)%20basis.%20India%20is%20the%205th%20largest%20and%20there%20is%20speculation%20that%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20decade%2C%20it%20may%20overtake%20Germany.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EGrowth%20in%20Russia%20and%20Brazil%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20second%20decade%20has%20been%20disappointing.%20South%20Africa%2C%20has%20shown%20a%20preference%20to%20approach%20the%20IMF%2C%20despite%20the%20onerous%20conditionalities%20of%20its%20loans.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20impact%2C%20probably%20the%20inclusion%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20might%20be%20transformative%20given%20its%20particular%20importance%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20oil%20exporter.%20But%20overall%2C%20just%20bringing%20in%20more%20countries%20to%20add%20strength%20might%20not%20be%20that%20effective%2C%20because%20the%20individual%20performance%20of%20these%20emerging%20economies%20is%20quite%20different.%20The%20NDB%20has%20provided%20loans%20of%20nearly%20%2432%20billion%20till%20now.%20While%20this%20sounds%20impressive%2C%20it%20pales%20in%20comparison%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20bilateral%20lending%20of%20almost%20%241%20trillion.%20So%20if%20just%20China%20and%20India%20agree%20to%20cooperate%20on%20the%20issues%20related%20to%20trade%2C%20cross-border%20payments%2C%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20climate%20change%20etc.%20that%20would%20alone%20have%20a%20completely%20transformative%20impact%20on%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20BRICS.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnarendra-modi-xi-jinping-india-china-south-africa%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Who%20Will%20Move%20First%3F%E2%80%99%3A%20Is%20a%20Modi-Xi%20Meeting%20on%20the%20Cards%20at%20Johannesburg%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20current%20situation%20is%20an%20ideal%20time%20for%20a%20reckoning%20of%20the%20international%20relations%20of%20the%20BRICS%20nations%20and%20in%20particular%20of%20their%20often%20problematic%20relations%20with%20the%20West.%20An%20unremitting%20problem%20with%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Famid-sanctions-against-russia-brics-can-lead-the-change-towards-national-currency-payments%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBRICS%20financial%20institutions%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20transparency%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cspan%3E%20The%20other%20glaring%20problem%20is%20intense%20internal%20dissension%2C%20particularly%20between%20India%20and%20China.%20If%20the%20BRICS%20nations%20are%20to%20effectively%20challenge%20Western%20dominance%20in%20the%20management%20of%20financial%20institutions%2C%20they%20must%20embrace%20the%20multilateralism%20that%20the%20grouping%20offers%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20disparate%20situational%20objectives%20that%20each%20is%20pursuing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETaking%20lessons%20from%20the%20G7%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20been%20encumbered%20by%20geo-political%20statements%20and%20positions%2C%20BRICS%20must%20avoid%20the%20politicisation%20of%20its%20agenda.%20Member%20nations%20must%20continue%20to%20build%20voices%20around%20the%20economy%2C%20development%2C%20prosperity%20goals%20and%20multilateral%20systems.%20Overall%2C%20the%20momentum%20of%20the%20BRICS%20forum%20is%20gaining%20both%20in%20terms%20of%20global%20reach%20and%20approach.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fvaishali-basu-sharma%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVaishali%20Basu%20Sharma%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20an%20analyst%20of%20strategic%20and%20economic%20affairs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692619253000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21155630%2FNDB-HQ-LOGO.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fissues-focus-brics-summit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20current%20situation%20is%20an%20ideal%20time%20for%20a%20reckoning%20of%20the%20international%20relations%20of%20the%20BRICS%20nations%20and%20in%20particular%20of%20their%20often%20problematic%20relations%20with%20the%20West.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fissues-focus-brics-summit%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ayushmann%3A%20You%20will%20get%20to%20see%20Pooja%20in%20real%20flesh%20and%20blood%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692619080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102909322%2Cimgsize-36790.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fayushmann-khurrana-on-dream-girl-2-you-will-get-to-see-pooja-in-real-flesh-and-blood-exclusive%2Farticleshow%2F102909956.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102909956.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAyushmann%20Khurrana%20is%20set%20to%20star%20in%20the%20sequel%20of%20his%20hit%20film%20'Dream%20Gi