ficant%20moment%20in%20the%20history%20of%20higher%20education%20in%20India%20as%20academic%20freedom%20has%20never%20been%20an%20issue%20important%20enough%20for%20teachers%20or%20students%20to%20take%20this%20extreme%20step%20of%20halting%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20not%20see%20teachers%20and%20students%20of%20the%20Jodhpur%20University%20organising%20a%20strike%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fjodhpur-university-rajshree-ranawat-suspended-nivedita%5C%22%3ERajshri%20Ranawat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20English%20teacher%2C%20was%20suspended%20for%20holding%20a%20seminar%20and%20inviting%20scholars%20like%20Nivedita%20Menon.%20She%20had%20to%20fight%20a%20battle%20on%20her%20own%20against%20her%20suspension.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20academic%20community%20of%20the%20Central%20University%20of%20Kerala%20did%20not%20make%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fprofessor-gilbert-sebastian-central-university-of-kerala-suspension-rss%5C%22%3Esuspension%20of%20Gilbert%20Sebastian%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20issue.%20He%20was%20penalised%20for%20teaching%20a%20class%20on%20fascism.%20Neither%20have%20we%20heard%20any%20action%20from%20the%20teaching%20community%20of%20the%20institute%20of%20Kolhapur%2C%20which%20sent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F1052201%2Frevoke-kolhapur-professors-forced-leave-who-said-rapists-could-be-from-any-religion-say-academics%5C%22%3ENiranjana%20Desai%20on%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20telling%20her%20students%20that%20rapists%20could%20be%20from%20any%20community.%20We%20have%20also%20not%20heard%20about%20any%20protest%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fpune%2Fsymbiosis-professor-held-pune-objectionable-remarks-hindu-deities-8875111%2F%5C%22%3Efaculty%20member%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Symbiosis%20College%20of%20Arts%20and%20Commerce%20who%20was%20arrested%20and%20suspended%20for%20a%20talk%20he%20gave%20in%20his%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20numerous%20violations%20of%20academic%20freedom%20in%20universities%20and%20colleges%20across%20India%2C%20but%20no%20such%20strikes%20were%20organised%20by%20the%20teaching%20community%2C%20despite%20their%20history%20of%20protesting%20against%20various%20service-related%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20students%20and%20teachers%20of%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20(JNU)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fgallery%2F2016%2F2%2F18%2Fnew-delhi-protest-thousands-call-for-students-freedom%5C%22%3Eprotested%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016%20after%20its%20students%20were%20attacked%20during%20a%20protest.%20But%20after%20that%20we%20have%20seen%20how%20academics%20watched%20anxiously%20while%20their%20colleagues%20were%20being%20attacked%2C%20penalised%2C%20and%20even%20jailed%20to%20defend%20their%20right%20to%20academic%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fdelhi%2Fjnu-sedition-case-chargesheet-kanhaiya-kumar-umar-khalid-5537648%2F%5C%22%3EJNU%20incident%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20treated%20more%20as%20a%20political%20reaction%20to%20a%20political%20attack%20even%20when%20we%20know%20that%20it%20was%20essentially%20a%20matter%20of%20academic%20freedom.%20Students%20like%20Kanhaiya%20Kumar%2C%20Umar%20Khalid%2C%20Anirban%20Bhattacharya%2C%20Rama%20Naga%20and%20others%20were%20attacked%20for%20having%20organised%20a%20meeting%20at%20the%20campus%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20Kashmir.%20However%2C%20beyond%20its%20strong%20and%20vocal%20protest%2C%20we%20have%20not%20seen%20the%20teaching%20community%20convey%20to%20the%20authorities%20that%20teaching%20is%20meaningless%20if%20academic%20freedom%20is%20compromised.%20So%2C%20if%20a%20teacher%20is%20persecuted%20for%20his%20research%2C%20teaching%20cannot%20go%20on%20as%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20step%20that%20makes%20the%20protest%20by%20Ashoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20academic%20community%20extraordinary.%20It%20centres%20the%20question%20of%20academic%20freedom%20in%20a%20way%20not%20done%20before.%20Ashoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20academic%20community%20needs%20to%20be%20supported%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fashoka-university-sabyasachi-das-pulapre-balakrishnan%5C%22%3Espirited%20defence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Sabyasachi%20Das.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fashoka-is-falling-short-of-its-declared-vision-300-academics-express-solidarity-with-sabyasachi-das%5C%22%3EAshoka%20Is%20Falling%20Short%20of%20Its%20Declared%20Vision%E2%80%99%3A%20300%2B%20Academics%20Express%20Solidarity%20With%20Sabyasachi%20Das%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20case%20of%20Ashoka%20University%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%20all%20the%20centres%20and%20departments%20of%20the%20university%20have%20come%20out%20in%20support%20of%20Das%2C%20who%20was%20forced%20to%20resign%20after%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fashoka-university-facultys-research-paper-on-bjp-manipulation-in-2019-election-triggers-row%5C%22%3Eresearch%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20possible%20manipulation%20of%20the%20election%20process%20in%20the%202019%20general%20elections%20was%20attacked%20by%20the%20members%20of%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP).%20Students%20and%20teachers%20have%20questioned%20the%20stand%20of%20the%20management%2C%20asking%20it%20to%20reinstate%20Das.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20research%20paper%20argued%20that%20there%20was%20a%20possibility%20that%20the%20election%20process%20was%20manipulated%20in%20closely%20contested%20seats%20to%20benefit%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20research%20paper%20created%20excitement%20within%20academic%20circles%2C%20its%20sampling%2C%20methodology%2C%20and%20findings%20were%20under%20examination.%20But%20the%20BJP%20members%20took%20offence%20and%20unleashed%20an%20online%20attack%20on%20Das.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20us%20have%20faced%20such%20an%20attack%20for%20writing%20an%20article%20or%20making%20a%20speech.%20However%2C%20in%20most%20of%20the%20cases%2C%20the%20university%20administration%20did%20not%20think%20it%20necessary%20to%20intervene.%20But%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Das%2C%20the%20members%20of%20the%20governing%20board%20intervened%2C%20forcing%20the%20administration%20to%20institute%20an%20enquiry%20to%20look%20into%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20research%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20extraordinary%20step%20by%20the%20university%20administration%20to%20have%20even%20thought%20about%20such%20a%20step.%20Looking%20into%20the%20quality%20of%20a%20research%20paper%20and%20whether%20it%20is%20academically%20sound%20or%20not%20is%20not%20the%20job%20of%20the%20administration.%20This%20is%20best%20done%20by%20peers.%20But%20here%2C%20the%20governing%20board%20thought%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20it%20was%20entering%20an%20area%20which%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20in%20its%20purview.%20It%20was%20attempting%20to%20dictate%20to%20the%20teachers%20how%20research%20should%20be%20conducted.%20We%20learnt%20that%20there%20were%20well-intentioned%20suggestions%20made%20to%20Das%20to%20change%20the%20title%20of%20the%20paper%20to%20make%20it%20sound%20more%20neutral%20and%20ask%20him%20to%20refrain%20from%20talking%20about%20it%20till%20the%20enquiry%20was%20over.%20He%20was%20free%20to%20teach%2C%20however.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20was%20absurd%20and%20made%20no%20sense.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20administration%20was%20effectively%20telling%20the%20academic%20community%20to%20not%20trust%20Das.%20What%20was%20to%20be%20investigated%20in%20the%20paper%3F%20Das%20had%20already%20invited%20the%20academic%20community%20for%20comments%20and%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20case%2C%20the%20governing%20board%20interfered%20with%20academic%20work%20which%20was%20outside%20its%20domain.%20Is%20there%20any%20guarantee%20it%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20restrict%20the%20university%20from%20inviting%20people%20who%20are%20disliked%20by%20the%20current%20regime%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20governing%20board%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20succumbs%20to%20pressure%20from%20the%20regime.%20It%20chose%20to%20part%20ways%20with%20a%20celebrated%20scholar%20like%20Pratap%20Bhanu%20Mehta%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Famid-ashoka-university-row-a-look-at-professors-who-quit-their-posts-in-protest-8896760%2F%5C%22%3Ewho%20had%20consistently%20questioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20ruling%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%20there%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F990333%2Fdismantling-the-labyrinth-what-i-learnt-about-power-and-privilege-when-i-quit-ashoka-in-2016%5C%22%3Ewere%20dismissals%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20faculty%20member%20and%20another%20employee%20for%20their%20being%20part%20of%20a%20petition%20on%20Kashmir.%20On%20both%20these%20occasions%20there%20were%20murmurs%20of%20protest%20but%20no%20decisive%20step%20taken%20by%20the%20university%20community%20to%20defend%20its%20space%20which%20is%20academic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsafeguarding-academic-freedom-is-the-bedrock-of-indias-constitutional-morality%5C%22%3ESafeguarding%20Academic%20Freedom%20Is%20the%20Bedrock%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitutional%20Morality%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnother%20line%20of%20argument%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20academic%20community%20at%20Ashoka%20University%20can%20only%20direct%20its%20protests%20towards%20the%20governing%20board.%20There%20is%20an%20ongoing%20debate%20in%20the%20public%20sphere%20regarding%20the%20wisdom%20of%20targeting%20these%20board%20members.%20The%20argument%20put%20forth%20is%20as%20follows%3A%20It%20was%20only%20due%20to%20pressure%20from%20members%20of%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20that%20the%20board%20was%20compelled%20to%20take%20action.%20They%20are%20acting%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20safeguarding%20the%20university%2C%20and%20they%20believe%20that%20a%20small%20sacrifice%20can%20be%20made%20for%20greater%20objectives.%20It%E2%80%99s%20important%20not%20to%20cast%20blame%20on%20the%20governing%20board%2C%20as%20we%20must%20acknowledge%20that%20they%20had%20good%20intentions%20when%20they%20established%20this%20university%2C%20with%20the%20betterment%20of%20liberal%20education%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccountability%20should%20be%20placed%2C%20the%20argument%20goes%20on%2C%20at%20the%20regime%E2%80%99s%20doorstep%20for%20coercing%20the%20administration%20into%20taking%20this%20unwelcome%20step.%20The%20governing%20board%20has%20numerous%20responsibilities%20to%20sustain%20the%20university%2C%20unlike%20Das%2C%20who%20appears%20to%20be%20primarily%20concerned%20with%20his%20academic%20integrity.%20These%20board%20members%20are%20taking%20on%20a%20difficult%20task%20for%20a%20higher%20purpose%20and%20are%20willing%20to%20accept%20being%20seen%20as%20compromised%20individuals.%20It%E2%80%99s%20crucial%20to%20remember%20that%20they%20have%20been%20pressured%20into%20taking%20this%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20argument%20sounds%20persuasive%20and%20is%20also%20true%20to%20a%20great%20extent.%20Das%20was%20not%20served%20with%20a%20notice%20proactively%20by%20the%20board.%20It%20didn%E2%80%99t%20seem%20to%20have%20any%20problem%20with%20the%20paper.%20But%20it%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20disregard%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20ruling%20regime%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20university.%20Keeping%20in%20mind%20the%20interest%20of%20hundreds%20of%20students%2C%20scores%20of%20faculty%20members%20and%20the%20image%20of%20the%20university%2C%20it%20had%20to%20take%20the%20unwelcome%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20should%20we%20accept%20this%20line%20of%20argument%3F%20Remember%20how%20Rutgers%20University%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftwitter-faceoff-rutgers-university-backs-controversial-historian-audrey-truschke-netizens-react%2Farticleshow%2F81412939.cms%5C%22%3Ebacked%3C%2Fa%3E%20Audrey%20Truschke%20when%20she%20was%20attacked%20on%20social%20media%20by%20some%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20groups%E2%80%99%20for%20her%20so-called%20%E2%80%9CHinduphobic%20statements%E2%80%9D%3F%20The%20university%20could%20have%20easily%20distanced%20itself%20from%20her.%20However%2C%20it%20did%20not.%20That%20is%20how%20the%20administrators%20of%20a%20university%20are%20expected%20to%20behave.%20They%20have%20to%20defend%20their%20faculty%20and%20students%20from%20external%20pressure%20and%20attack%20and%20not%20the%20other%20way%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20community%20must%20demand%20answers%20from%20its%20board.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20the%20fight%20isn%E2%80%99t%20against%20the%20government%20as%20there%20is%20no%20government%20involvement%20here.%20Let%20the%20board%20members%20explain%20their%20actions%20against%20Das%20and%20provide%20insights%20into%20their%20previous%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20encouraging%20to%20see%20the%20faculty%20members%20and%20students%20of%20Ashoka%20University%20rising%20to%20the%20occasion%20to%20fight%20for%20academic%20freedom.%20That%20it%20was%20not%20done%20on%20earlier%20occasions%20should%20not%20make%20it%20any%20less%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fapoorvanand%5C%22%3EApoorvanand%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20at%20Delhi%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692611114000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F03%2FAshoka-University.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fashoka-university-strike-academic-freedom-sabyasachi-das%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20have%20been%20numerous%20violations%20of%20academic%20freedom%20in%20universities%20and%20colleges%20across%20India.%20But%20the%20Ashoka%20teaching%20community's%20response%20to%20Sabyasachi%20Das's%20resignation%20deserves%20praise.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fashoka-university-strike-academic-freedom-sabyasachi-das%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mumbai%20Police%20EOW%20lodges%20FIR%20against%20Rahul%20Yadav%2C%20issues%20lookout%20notice%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692609658000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2016-05%2F19%2Ffull%2F1463674404-8366.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fmumbai-police-eow-lodges-fir-against-rahul-yadav-issues-lookout-notice-123082100371_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20complainant%20in%20the%20case%20is%20Rajasthan-based%20Vikas%20Om%20Prakas%20Noval%2C%20a%20Rajasthan-based%20director%20of%20the%20Interspace%20Communication%20Private%20Limited%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fmumbai-police-eow-lodges-fir-against-rahul-yadav-issues-lookout-notice-123082100371_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fmumbai-police-eow-lodges-fir-against-rahul-yadav-issues-lookout-notice-123082100371_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fmumbai-police-eow-lodges-fir-against-rahul-yadav-issues-lookout-notice-123082100371_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Home%20Ministry%20Officials%20Top%20List%20of%20Complaints%20Received%20By%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21132433%2FCentral-vigilance-commission-logo.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cvc.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FARR2022.pdf%5C%22%3Elatest%20annual%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20(CVC)%20said%20that%20home%20affairs%20ministry%20employees%20made%20up%20the%20largest%20target%20of%20complaints%20it%20received%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20a%20total%20of%201%2C15%2C203%20complaints%20it%20received%20against%20Union%20government%20employees%2C%20the%20CVC%20said%20that%2046%2C643%20(~41%25)%20were%20against%20home%20affairs%20ministry%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20railways%20sector%20was%20at%20a%20distant%20second%20with%2010%2C580%20(9%25)%20complaints%20against%20its%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBanks%E2%80%9D%20employees%20were%20a%20source%20of%208%2C129%20complaints%2C%20the%20Delhi%20government%20of%207%2C370%20and%20%E2%80%9CCoal%E2%80%9D%20of%204%2C304.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CVC%20is%20an%20apex%20anti-corruption%20agency%20that%20oversees%20the%20vigilance%20administration%20of%20Union%20government%20organisations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESet%20up%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cvc.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Far2001.pdf%5C%22%3Espirit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cadministration%20%5Bcannot%5D%20be%20a%20judge%20of%20its%20own%20conduct%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20CVC%20is%20not%20controlled%20by%20any%20Union%20ministry%20and%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cvc.gov.in%2F%3Fq%3Dfaq%5C%22%3Eresponsible%20only%20to%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20functions%2C%20it%20provides%20%E2%80%98vigilance%20clearances%E2%80%99%20to%20certain%20senior%20government%20officials%20and%20processes%20complaints%20against%20government%20employees%2C%20following%20which%20it%20communicates%20its%20advice%20on%20action%20to%20be%20taken%20in%20appropriate%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20commission%20said%20in%20its%20most%20recent%20annual%20report%20that%20there%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20deviations%E2%80%9D%20or%20non-compliance%20with%20its%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20some%20cases%20of%20officers%20covered%20under%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction%2C%20either%20the%20prescribed%20consultation%20mechanism%20with%20the%20Commission%20was%20not%20adhered%20to%2C%20or%20the%20authorities%20concerned%20did%20not%20accept%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20stated%20in%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20there%20have%20been%20instances%20where%20the%20advice%20tendered%20by%20the%20Commission%20has%20been%20substantially%20diluted%20without%20approaching%20the%20Commission%20for%20reconsideration%20of%20its%20advice%2C%20as%20per%20extant%20procedure%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20continued%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20the%20CVC%20gave%20of%20improper%20following%20of%20procedure%20with%20its%20advice%20was%20the%20delaying%20of%20taking%20action%20against%20some%20delinquent%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20organisations%20take%20more%20than%20the%20prescribed%20time%20for%20implementation%20of%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%20which%20includes%20delay%20in%20issuance%20of%20charge%20sheet.%20Sometimes%2C%20the%20delinquent%20officer%20is%20allowed%20to%20retire%2C%20and%20the%20misconduct%20becomes%20time%20barred%20for%20initiation%20of%20departmental%20action%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20watchdog%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20appendices%20to%20its%20annual%20report%2C%20the%20commission%20recorded%20the%20type%20of%20punishment%20that%20was%20given%20to%20government%20employees%20from%20various%20sectors%20following%20penalty%20proceedings%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20Union%20home%20affairs%20ministry%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20that%20the%20following%20punishments%20were%20given%20to%20its%20employees%20after%20major%20penalty%20proceedings%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21131839%2FMHA-major-penalties-1024x477.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22666%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21131839%2FMHA-major-penalties-1024x477.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21131839%2FMHA-major-penalties-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21131839%2FMHA-major-penalties.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668955%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22310%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20cvc.gov.in%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20majority%20of%20employees%20in%20these%20cases%20had%20no%20action%20taken%20against%20them%2C%20unspecified%20%E2%80%9Cmajor%20penalties%E2%80%9D%20handed%20out%2C%20or%20were%20given%20warnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20following%20are%20the%20results%20of%20minor%20proceedings%20against%20home%20affairs%20employees%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21132043%2FMHA-minor-penalties-1024x477.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22606%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21132043%2FMHA-minor-penalties-1024x477.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21132043%2FMHA-minor-penalties-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21132043%2FMHA-minor-penalties.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668956%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22282%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20cvc.gov.in%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20action%20was%20taken%20against%20employees%20in%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20minor%20penalty%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20home%20affairs%20ministry%20is%20currently%20led%20by%20BJP%20leader%20Amit%20Shah.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692609359000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21132433%2FCentral-vigilance-commission-logo.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmajority-of-complaints-to-cvc-made-against-home-affairs-ministry%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20its%20annual%20report%20for%202022%2C%20the%20commission%20also%20listed%20various%20instances%20of%20non-compliance%20with%20its%20advice%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20types%20of%20punishment%20given%20to%20officials%20in%20penalty%20proceedings.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmajority-of-complaints-to-cvc-made-against-home-affairs-ministry%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Bad%20Advice%20Led%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20To%20Make%20Mistakes%20in%20Handling%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20Issue%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F02163603%2Frajiv-gandhi.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENext%20only%20to%20Shah%20Bano%20in%20the%20denigration%20of%20the%20former%20PM%20is%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20issue.%20In%20October%201985%2C%20Arun%20Nehru%20was%20made%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20internal%20security.%20This%20was%20widely%20seen%20as%20evidence%20of%20his%20huge%20political%20clout.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20Today%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%2031%20October%201985%20described%20him%20as%20%E2%80%98the%20fastest%20rising%20star%20in%20the%20firmament%20of%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20government%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20resignation%20of%20Narayan%20Datt%20Tiwari%20as%20chief%20minister%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20on%20his%20being%20elevated%20to%20the%20Union%20cabinet%2C%20Arun%20Nehru%20personally%20picked%20and%20promoted%20the%20relatively%20unknown%20Vir%20Bahadur%20Singh%20as%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20chief%20minister%20in%20September%201985.%20There%20was%2C%20said%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20Today%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(31%20October%201985)%2C%20an%20%E2%80%98awed%20realization%E2%80%99%20of%20Arun%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20hold%20over%20party%20affairs.%20For%20his%20part%2C%20Arun%20Nehru%20believed%20that%20the%20best%20route%20to%20winning%20the%20Hindu%20vote%20was%20by%20opening%20the%20locks%20that%20had%20been%20placed%20in%20December%201949%20on%20the%20gates%20leading%20to%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%20This%20sixteenth-century%20mosque%20had%20become%20the%20focus%20of%20a%20localized%20dispute%20over%20ownership%20rights%20dating%20back%20to%20the%20mid-nineteenth%20century%2C%20based%20on%20the%20claim%20that%20the%20mosque%20had%20been%20built%20on%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Lord%20Ram%20%E2%80%93%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi.%20At%20the%20time%20(1985)%2C%20this%20local%20dispute%20had%20no%20national%20reverberations%20despite%20the%20gates%20being%20locked%20up%20thirty-five%20long%20years%20earlier.%20But%20Arun%20Nehru%2C%20with%20his%20local%20roots%2C%20having%20studied%20at%20a%20Lucknow%20school%20and%20college%20in%20proximity%20to%20Ayodhya%2C%20had%20an%20awareness%20of%20the%20potential%20of%20this%20issue%20that%20barely%20registered%2C%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20on%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20consciousness.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20400px)%2085vw%2C%20400px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21134743%2FMemoirs-of-a-Maverick-high-res.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21134743%2FMemoirs-of-a-Maverick-high-res.jpeg%20796w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21134743%2FMemoirs-of-a-Maverick-high-res-199x300.jpeg%20199w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21134743%2FMemoirs-of-a-Maverick-high-res-679x1024.jpeg%20679w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668965%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22603%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EMemoirs%20of%20a%20Maverick%3A%20The%20First%20Fifty%20Years%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EJuggernaut%20(August%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20chief%20minister%20visited%20Ayodhya%20in%20December%201985%20and%20stirred%20up%20a%20hornets%E2%80%99%20nest%20by%20ordering%20that%20all%20files%20relating%20to%20the%20closure%20of%20the%20gates%20be%20reviewed.%20Meanwhile%2C%20a%20case%20was%20filed%20by%20a%20private%20party%20before%20the%20sessions%20judge%2C%20Faizabad%2C%20to%20reopen%20the%20locks.%20The%20gravamen%20of%20his%20plea%20was%20that%20the%20locks%20had%20been%20placed%20in%20December%201949%20by%20executive%20rather%20than%20judicial%20order.%20The%20sessions%20judge%20scheduled%20an%20immediate%20hearing%3B%20after%20the%20local%20police%20and%20district%20magistrate%20testified%20they%20did%20not%20apprehend%20a%20law%20and%20order%20problem%20if%20the%20locks%20were%20opened%2C%20the%20sessions%20judge%20ordered%20their%20reopening.%20Within%20minutes%20of%20the%20order%20being%20passed%20in%20Faizabad%2C%20the%20locks%20at%20Ayodhya%2C%20closed%20for%20over%20thirty-five%20years%2C%20were%20broken%20open%20and%2C%20in%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20an%20orchestrated%20move%2C%20huge%20numbers%20of%20Hindu%20devotees%20poured%20into%20the%20masjid%20premises.%20Clearly%2C%20the%20administration%20was%20in%20cohorts%20with%20the%20district%20sessions%20court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20judgment%20was%20quickly%20challenged%20by%20a%20private%20Muslim%20party%20before%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20High%20Court%2C%20and%20the%20state%20government%20impleaded%20itself%20into%20the%20court%20proceedings.%20For%20the%20saffron%20forces%2C%20wilting%20in%20the%20penumbra%20after%20their%20massive%20defeat%20in%20the%201984%20elections%2C%20this%20was%20the%20opportunity%20to%20stir%20the%20communal%20cauldron%20to%20make%20a%20political%20comeback.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20since%20been%20held%20by%20most%20public%20opinion%20that%20it%20was%20at%20the%20PM%E2%80%99s%20behest%20that%20the%20locks%20were%20opened%2C%20whereas%20RG%20maintained%20that%20he%20was%20completely%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20this%20conspiracy%20to%20open%20the%20locks%20and%20learnt%20about%20it%20only%20after%20it%20was%20an%20accomplished%20fact.%20There%20has%20always%20been%20intense%20speculation%20as%20to%20how%20such%20a%20momentous%20change%20in%20the%20status%20quo%20could%20have%20been%20undertaken%20without%20his%20knowledge%20and%20explicit%20sanction.%20Commentators%20reasoned%20then%20%E2%80%93%20and%20their%20argument%20continues%20till%20today%2C%20nearly%20four%20decades%20later%20%E2%80%93%20that%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20having%20got%20the%20Muslim%20vote%20in%20his%20kitty%20through%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20matter%2C%20had%20now%20decided%20to%20also%20grab%20the%20Hindu%20vote%20bank%20by%20opening%20the%20locks%20at%20Ayodhya.%20RG%20always%20maintained%20that%20he%20had%20no%20prior%20information%20about%20what%20Arun%20Nehru%20was%20up%20to%2C%20and%20this%20is%20confirmed%20by%20Wajahat%20Habibullah%20in%20his%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20Years%20with%20Rajiv%3A%20Triumph%20and%20Tragedy%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(Westland%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%202020).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20no%20executive%20order%20by%20which%20the%20PM%20could%20reverse%20the%20order%20to%20open%20the%20locks%20since%20it%20was%20a%20judicial%20order.%20Huge%20communal%20tension%20would%20have%20built%20up%20had%20he%20gone%20to%20the%20High%20Court.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20a%20petition%20against%20the%20sessions%20judge%E2%80%99s%20order%20had%20already%20been%20filed%20in%20the%20High%20Court%20and%20was%20soon%20followed%20by%20the%20Sunni%20Waqf%20Board%20and%20the%20government%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20impleading%20themselves%20as%20affected%20parties.%20But%20going%20to%20the%20courts%20is%20invariably%20a%20time-consuming%20business.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20the%20PM%20ordered%20an%20internal%20party%20enquiry%20into%20the%20respective%20roles%20of%20Arun%20Nehru%20and%20M.L.%20Fotedar%20in%20the%20imbroglio.%20The%20enquiry%20exonerated%20Fotedar%20but%20pinned%20the%20responsibility%20on%20Arun%20Nehru.%20Accordingly%2C%20Arun%20Nehru%20was%20first%20sidelined%20and%20then%20dropped%20summarily%20from%20the%20Council%20of%20Ministers%20in%20October%201986.%20For%20him%20to%20fall%20so%20precipitately%20within%20a%20year%20of%20being%20hailed%20as%20the%20power%20behind%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20throne%20was%20punishment%20enough.%20Indeed%2C%20he%20had%20had%20a%20heart%20attack%20at%20Dachigam%20in%20Kashmir%20in%20April%201986%20and%20the%20first%20sign%20that%20all%20was%20not%20well%20between%20him%20and%20his%20cousin%20was%20that%20the%20PM%20pointedly%20declined%20to%20go%20to%20his%20bedside%20and%20sent%20just%20his%20physician%20instead.%20(There%20was%20also%20Arun%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20nefarious%20interference%20in%20the%20Bofors%20matter%2C%20touched%20upon%20in%20the%20next%20section%20on%20Bofors%2C%20and%20further%20elaborated%20in%20the%20companion%20volume.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20the%20immediate%20kerfuffle%20was%20over%2C%20it%20seemed%20through%20most%20of%20the%20succeeding%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20(mid-1986%20to%20end%201988)%20that%20the%20political%20turbulence%20over%20Babri%20Masjid-Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20simmered%20rather%20than%20boiled%20over.%20It%20was%20only%20once%20V.P.%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20National%20Front%20emerged%20as%20a%20strong%20contender%20for%20the%201989%20elections%20that%20its%20partner%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20stoked%20the%20dispute%20into%20a%20national%20matter.%20By%201989%2C%20it%20was%20evident%20that%20the%20issue%20was%20going%20to%20play%20a%20major%20role%20in%20determining%20the%20outcome%20at%20the%20hustings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20this%20point%20R.K.%20Dhawan%20was%20brought%20into%20the%20PMO.%20Also%2C%20Sheila%20Dikshit%20was%20appointed%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20parliamentary%20affairs%2C%20with%20an%20office%20in%20the%20PMO%20and%20became%20the%20channel%20through%20which%20partisan%20party%20considerations%20began%20flowing%20into%20decision-making.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20firewall%20provided%20by%20Gopi%20Arora%20was%20absent%20as%20he%20had%20been%20shifted%20out%20of%20the%20PMO%20in%20late%201987.%20The%20political%20advisers%20were%20brought%20in%20because%20it%20was%20believed%20that%20it%20was%20their%20absence%20from%20the%20scene%20over%20the%20past%20four%20years%20that%20was%20the%20precise%20reason%20for%20the%20growing%20dissidence%20in%20the%20party%20and%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20tumbling%20image%20in%20the%20media%20and%20public%20opinion.%20As%20Suneet%20had%20warned%20us%2C%20with%20Dhawan%E2%80%99s%20entry%2C%20things%20really%20changed.%20Once%20decision-making%20in%20policy%20got%20entangled%20with%20party%20and%20electoral%20considerations%2C%20the%20PM%E2%80%99s%20standing%20only%20deteriorated%20further.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20most%20egregious%20example%20was%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eshilanyas%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(ground-breaking%20and%20foundation%20stone-laying%20ceremony)%20at%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20site%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20election%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20the%20Dhawan%E2%80%93Fotedar%20duo%3B%20it%20did%20nothing%20to%20attract%20the%20hard%20Hindu%20vote%20to%20the%20PM%20but%20definitively%20alienated%20Muslim%20and%20left-liberal%20opinion.%20While%20the%20PM%E2%80%99s%20own%20commitment%20to%20not%20allow%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20mosque%20remained%20firm%20and%20consistent%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eshilanyas%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20arranged%20amounted%20to%20imitation%20of%20the%20saffron%20forces%20and%20appeasement%20of%20the%20majority%20community.%20He%20stepped%20on%20to%20the%20ground%20prepared%20by%20the%20Opposition%20and%20the%20rationale%20of%20his%20action%20(saving%20the%20mosque%20but%20promising%20a%20grand%20temple)%20was%20lost%20on%20those%20who%20wanted%20the%20mosque%20gone%20and%20even%20on%20those%20who%20desperately%20wanted%20the%20mosque%20saved.%20It%20was%20a%20classic%20case%20of%20being%20hoist%20by%20his%20own%20petard%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20persons%20fundamentally%20responsible%20for%20this%20were%20the%20%E2%80%98politicos%E2%80%99%20inducted%20into%20the%20PMO%20in%20early%201989%20to%20allegedly%20lend%20political%20heft%20to%20the%20PM.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20only%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20was%20responsible%20for%20accepting%20irresponsible%20advice%20that%20was%20anathema%20to%20his%20moral%20principles%20and%20enduring%20belief%20in%20secularism.%20Because%20he%20imitated%20the%20Opposition%20instead%20of%20confronting%20them%2C%20all%20his%20many%20positive%20initiatives%20were%20lost%20in%20the%20electoral%20tornado%20that%20blew%20across%20the%20country.%20It%20was%20the%20only%20time%20I%20saw%20him%20looking%20shaken%20and%20jaded%2C%20his%20normal%20self-confidence%20and%20smiling%20demeanour%20having%20deserted%20him.%20He%20knew%20he%20was%20fighting%20a%20losing%20battle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20conclusion%20does%20one%20draw%20from%20this%20sad%20tale%3F%20Had%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20stuck%20to%20his%20basic%20values%20and%20fought%20the%201989%20elections%20on%20his%20secular%20convictions%20and%20his%20many%20constructive%20nation-building%20initiatives%2C%20such%20as%20Panchayati%20Raj%2C%20and%20not%20allowed%20himself%20to%20be%20led%20to%20fighting%20the%20elections%20on%20turf%20prepared%20by%20his%20opponents%2C%20he%20might%20have%20prevailed.%20Of%20course%2C%20he%20would%20have%20lost%20his%20commanding%20lead%20of%201984%20but%20would%20probably%20have%20emerged%20in%20end%201989%20with%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ea%20majority%2C%20however%20slight.%20By%20allowing%20himself%20to%20be%20misled%20by%20Dhawan%20%26amp%3B%20Co%20%E2%80%93%20for%20which%2C%20of%20course%2C%20he%20had%20only%20himself%20to%20blame%20%E2%80%93%20he%20allowed%20calumny%20to%20triumph%20over%20constructive%20nation-building.%20He%20also%20opened%20the%20door%20to%20the%20majoritarianism%20and%20authoritarianism%20now%20being%20inflicted%20on%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPerhaps%20neither%20hubris%20nor%20assassination%20would%20have%20overwhelmed%20him%20had%20he%20not%20had%20such%20a%20large%20and%20assured%20parliamentary%20majority%20on%20becoming%20prime%20minister.%20A%20humbler%20victory%20in%201984%20may%20have%20made%20him%20more%20cautious%20and%20circumspect%2C%20and%20more%20obliged%20to%20consult%20sidelined%20party%20veterans.%20But%20that%20was%20not%20how%20it%20turned%20out%20%E2%80%93%20and%20he%20eventually%20paid%20with%20his%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EExcerpted%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3EMemoirs%20of%20a%20Maverick%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20Mani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%2C%20with%20permission%20from%20Juggernaut.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692607527000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F02163603%2Frajiv-gandhi.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbad-advice-rajiv-gandhi-mistakes-babri-masjid%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20internal%20party%20enquiry%20found%20that%20Arun%20Nehru%20had%20played%20a%20role%20in%20getting%20the%20locks%20to%20the%20Masjid%20opened.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbad-advice-rajiv-gandhi-mistakes-babri-masjid%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Saudi%20Arabia%20border%20guards%20likely%20killed%20hundreds%20of%20unarmed%20migrants%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20report%20claims%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692606600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F768x432%2Fskynews-yemen-saudi-arabia_6257923.jpg%3F20230821104115%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsaudi-arabia-border-guards-likely-killed-hundreds-of-unarmed-migrants-crossing-from-yemen-in-recent-years-report-claims-12944443%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Saudi%20Arabian%20border%20guards%20launched%20mortars%20and%20fired%20machine%20guns%20at%20Ethiopians%20trying%20to%20cross%20into%20the%20country%20from%20Yemen%20and%20likely%20killed%20hundreds%20of%20unarmed%20migrants%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20a%20new%20report%20has%20claimed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A149%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsaudi-arabia-border-guards-likely-killed-hundreds-of-unarmed-migrants-crossing-from-yemen-in-recent-years-report-claims-12944443%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsaudi-arabia-border-guards-likely-killed-h